Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.57,0:00:59.66,Director,,0,0,0,,CÉLINE SCIAMMA: The film starts with a white screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.62,0:01:05.46,Director,,0,0,0,,And it starts in a totally literal way.\NIt chooses to examine the first mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.50,0:01:10.34,Director,,0,0,0,,The first sketch, visibly feminine.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.05,0:01:18.30,Director,,0,0,0,,The cinema screen as a canvas.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.43,0:01:22.18,Director,,0,0,0,,This literality is like a pact\Nmade with the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.14,0:01:28.94,Director,,0,0,0,,There is austerity and silence too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.99,0:01:40.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, my contours.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.24,0:01:42.74,Director,,0,0,0,,These eyes darting up and down...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.87,0:01:43.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The outline.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.99,0:01:46.29,Director,,0,0,0,,...are part of the journey\Nthat this situation takes,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.41,0:01:48.96,Director,,0,0,0,,the dynamic between\Nthe painter and the model.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.71,0:01:51.71,Director,,0,0,0,,The back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.17,0:01:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not too fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.96,0:01:55.17,Director,,0,0,0,,I really wanted to film it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.47,0:01:59.97,Director,,0,0,0,,The film is playful from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.09,0:02:01.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take time to look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.85,0:02:04.93,Director,,0,0,0,,Because it places the painter\Nin the position of the model.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.48,0:02:07.89,Director,,0,0,0,,And it creates the desire\Nto see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.35,0:02:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See how my arms are placed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.44,0:02:15.28,Director,,0,0,0,,And it instructs us\Nto spend time looking at her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.40,0:02:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.41,0:02:21.45,Director,,0,0,0,,If we obey,\Nwe see her clenching her hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.45,0:02:26.20,Director,,0,0,0,,And our darting eyes engage us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.37,0:02:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who brought that painting out?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.33,0:02:33.09,Director,,0,0,0,,Opposite her\Nthere is a mysterious painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.21,0:02:34.71,Director,,0,0,0,,It creates a desire to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.26,0:02:39.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it in storage.\NShouldn't l have?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.64,0:02:47.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you paint it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.35,0:02:51.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.44,0:02:54.90,Director,,0,0,0,,The first tracking shot of the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.48,0:02:57.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.61,0:03:00.91,Director,,0,0,0,,It looks simple, but we had to remove\Nall the furniture and all the human beings
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.03,0:03:02.24,Director,,0,0,0,,to show the desired image.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.37,0:03:03.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the title?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.41,0:03:07.16,Director,,0,0,0,,The title is spoken.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.24,0:03:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Portrait of a Lady on Fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.87,0:03:12.54,Director,,0,0,0,,Whereas it was written\Nto be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.89,0:03:26.97,Director,,0,0,0,,We jump to an action scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.98,0:03:32.19,Director,,0,0,0,,A scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.73,0:03:34.94,Director,,0,0,0,,...on the open sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.11,0:03:42.70,Director,,0,0,0,,It's the sort of scene\Nwhich demands all the crew's attention
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.82,0:03:44.24,Director,,0,0,0,,while it is being prepared,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.37,0:03:48.41,Director,,0,0,0,,checking the tide tables,\Nfinding the right boat, the extras.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.70,0:03:52.67,Director,,0,0,0,,It's a scene with danger,\Nit's a scene with a stunt
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.67,0:03:55.04,Director,,0,0,0,,with a lot of elements to film.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.09,0:04:02.51,Director,,0,0,0,,On the whole, these are the scenes\Nyou get asked about the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.39,0:04:06.68,Director,,0,0,0,,My response to this sequence\Nis quite simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.76,0:04:08.68,Director,,0,0,0,,I was thinking of Hergé, of {\i0}Tintin{\i1}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.81,0:04:10.64,Director,,0,0,0,,for the shot of the crate.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.02,0:04:18.94,Director,,0,0,0,,And I wanted the heroine\Nto jump into the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.07,0:04:21.94,Director,,0,0,0,,breaking with convention\Nfrom the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.07,0:04:24.49,Director,,0,0,0,,She jumps in feet first\Nand the film jumps in feet first.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.92,0:04:43.05,Director,,0,0,0,,We arrive on an island.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.38,0:04:47.26,Director,,0,0,0,,Some people have said to me,\Nperhaps we've left an island.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.14,0:04:51.64,Director,,0,0,0,,It's a very wide shot,\None of the widest in the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.77,0:04:55.23,Director,,0,0,0,,The start of a wonderful collaboration\Nbetween Claire Mathon and nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.10,0:04:59.07,Director,,0,0,0,,It's clearly also a nod to Jane Campion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.57,0:05:09.99,Director,,0,0,0,,The physicality of our heroine is\Nthe first thing we're aware of, her body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.87,0:05:12.33,Director,,0,0,0,,Her costume is heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.25,0:05:17.71,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,NOÉMIE MERLANT: That dress, that outfit, that costume\Nwas the first thing I had
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.83,0:05:19.25,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,to help me get into character.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.38,0:05:20.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where do I go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.92,0:05:22.92,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,Very heavy clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.09,0:05:25.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Head straight up to the trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.13,0:05:28.39,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,With lots of layers\Nand underlayers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.51,0:05:30.72,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,like the film itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.01,0:05:35.39,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,The oppression,\Nthe burden placed on women.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.60,0:05:39.94,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,So, it was quite a direct way\Nof getting into character.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.94,0:05:45.40,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,How, in spite of everything,\NMarianne inhabits this costume,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.53,0:05:48.24,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,finding her freedom in it\Nand making it her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.13,0:06:05.38,Director,,0,0,0,,SCIAMMA: A new dynamic begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.47,0:06:09.59,Director,,0,0,0,,A dynamic of sequence shots\Nand movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.76,0:06:12.26,Director,,0,0,0,,And especially a sound dynamic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.43,0:06:16.02,Director,,0,0,0,,There is a new face.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.10,0:06:18.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Marianne.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.44,0:06:19.52,Director,,0,0,0,,Likeable from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.60,0:06:21.69,Director,,0,0,0,,Luéna Bajrami.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.45,0:06:34.62,Director,,0,0,0,,Miraculously, we found\Nthe chateau in that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.62,0:06:38.37,Director,,0,0,0,,It brings the era to life\Nif you can find places
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.54,0:06:40.88,Director,,0,0,0,,which still contain\Nelements and echoes of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.30,0:06:47.21,Director,,0,0,0,,Places you want to look at
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.34,0:06:48.55,Director,,0,0,0,,and also adorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.51,0:06:55.39,Director,,0,0,0,,Here there is very little at play,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.51,0:06:57.81,Director,,0,0,0,,just the reverberating footsteps.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.93,0:07:00.35,Director,,0,0,0,,And the acoustics of a room\Nwhich will become key.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.03,0:07:15.49,Director,,0,0,0,,80% of the film takes place\Nin this studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.08,0:07:24.34,Director,,0,0,0,,It was a gamble to move into a space\Nand to decide to create rituals there
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.46,0:07:26.63,Director,,0,0,0,,and to film it differently every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.46,0:07:31.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a reception room.\NI've never seen it used.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.30,0:07:35.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you been here long?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.22,0:07:37.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.31,0:07:40.39,Director,,0,0,0,,We decided from the start\Nto have a minimal set.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.52,0:07:41.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you like it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.64,0:07:43.69,Director,,0,0,0,,With very few props.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.81,0:07:46.40,Director,,0,0,0,,Most of the furniture was purpose-built.\NThat bed, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.32,0:07:48.86,Director,,0,0,0,,And that crate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.98,0:07:51.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll let you get dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.28,0:07:54.53,Director,,0,0,0,,There isn't much ornamentation,\Nno worldly goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.16,0:07:58.99,Director,,0,0,0,,We didn't change\Nthe colour of the walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.12,0:08:00.62,Director,,0,0,0,,We built that fireplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.39,0:08:22.06,Director,,0,0,0,,Here the sound starts to build.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.18,0:08:24.15,Director,,0,0,0,,There is the sense\Nthat a storm is brewing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.61,0:08:28.44,Director,,0,0,0,,Something stirring in the distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.19,0:08:34.36,Director,,0,0,0,,Recreating the sound\Nwas quite complex too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.49,0:08:35.91,Director,,0,0,0,,We use a lot of contemporary notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.03,0:08:38.99,Director,,0,0,0,,I really like modern notes\Nwhich are...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.04,0:08:46.46,Director,,0,0,0,,All the electric sounds, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.58,0:08:48.42,Director,,0,0,0,,Planes high up in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.54,0:08:50.30,Director,,0,0,0,,as a soundtrack\Nto the 18th century scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.42,0:08:51.76,Director,,0,0,0,,There's the wind and the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.13,0:08:54.22,Director,,0,0,0,,And the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.18,0:09:00.93,Director,,0,0,0,,I wanted the character to smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.71,0:09:34.34,Director,,0,0,0,,We tried to instil faith\Nin the sequence shot
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.47,0:09:36.68,Director,,0,0,0,,and the tension\Nof the sequence shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.43,0:09:44.35,Director,,0,0,0,,The challenge of the lighting\Nwas the candles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.48,0:09:46.52,Director,,0,0,0,,We made a radical choice
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.64,0:09:48.65,Director,,0,0,0,,to have very few light sources
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.94,0:09:51.07,Director,,0,0,0,,and...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.36,0:09:55.36,Director,,0,0,0,,...to have very few candles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.49,0:09:57.11,Director,,0,0,0,,There is the fire in the rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.24,0:09:59.74,Director,,0,0,0,,But the actresses\Nare always topped
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.87,0:10:02.66,Director,,0,0,0,,by a network of lights\Nwhich follows them all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.54,0:10:07.75,Director,,0,0,0,,They are followed\Nby the sound and the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.79,0:10:46.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, l helped myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.91,0:10:48.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.96,0:10:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there any wine?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.67,0:10:53.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.19,0:11:14.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I be curious?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.65,0:11:22.11,Director,,0,0,0,,A horizontality is set up quite quickly\Nbetween the characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.24,0:11:24.70,Director,,0,0,0,,The discussions are frank\Nand to the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.83,0:11:26.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is your young mistress like?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.00,0:11:29.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know her well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.41,0:11:32.21,Director,,0,0,0,,The film has chosen not to toy\Nwith class hierarchies.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.33,0:11:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've been here three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.92,0:11:36.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She only arrived a few weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.75,0:11:38.92,Director,,0,0,0,,This is a dynamic\Nwhich will blossom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.05,0:11:40.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where from?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.34,0:11:41.88,Director,,0,0,0,,Into a sisterhood and a friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.01,0:11:43.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Benedictines.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.14,0:11:46.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has she left holy orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.18,0:11:50.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They brought her home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.89,0:11:55.02,Director,,0,0,0,,Sophie is a servant,\Nbut she doesn't act like one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.15,0:11:56.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her sister died.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.11,0:11:59.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was the one due to many?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.53,0:12:01.82,Director,,0,0,0,,She only appears in a scene\Nwhen she has something to add,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.95,0:12:04.24,Director,,0,0,0,,a plan, a role to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.37,0:12:06.78,Director,,0,0,0,,She's never incidental,\Nan accessory.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.91,0:12:08.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did disease take her?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.54,0:12:11.54,Director,,0,0,0,,We see her thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.09,0:12:18.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you manage it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.38,0:12:22.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Manage what?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.18,0:12:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To paint her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.89,0:12:27.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.14,0:12:29.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another painter was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.73,0:12:35.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wasn't able to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.44,0:12:36.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.61,0:12:43.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.50,0:12:55.00,Director,,0,0,0,,Here we discover the surroundings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.25,0:13:00.25,Director,,0,0,0,,And we are between two traditions:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.51,0:13:03.97,Director,,0,0,0,,Video games from the 1990s,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.09,0:13:06.30,Director,,0,0,0,,{\i0}Alone in the Dark{\i1},\Nthe point-and-click,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.47,0:13:08.35,Director,,0,0,0,,or more recently {\i0}Escape Room{\i1}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.47,0:13:11.77,Director,,0,0,0,,We discover all the objects\Nwhich will be used by the character.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.89,0:13:14.39,Director,,0,0,0,,And another tradition,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.35,0:13:17.06,Director,,0,0,0,,that of fantasy films.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.57,0:13:21.86,Director,,0,0,0,,Playing with mirrors\Nand perspective.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.98,0:13:23.82,Director,,0,0,0,,A desire, too, for inanimate objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.45,0:13:32.62,Director,,0,0,0,,A tracking shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.79,0:13:35.62,Director,,0,0,0,,Towards a canvas,\Nturned to face the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.79,0:13:41.80,Director,,0,0,0,,A choreography incorporating\Nthe wind, breath and footsteps.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.09,0:13:46.97,Director,,0,0,0,,Fear is often conveyed by sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.49,0:14:06.99,Director,,0,0,0,,The portrait with no face,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.07,0:14:11.91,Director,,0,0,0,,which acts as a link shot\Nwhich was written into the screenplay,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.08,0:14:13.12,Director,,0,0,0,,considered.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.33,0:14:18.08,Director,,0,0,0,,This dress without a head\Nwhich does now have feet
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.25,0:14:19.83,Director,,0,0,0,,but still not the right head.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.46,0:14:25.59,Director,,0,0,0,,We start to create a desire\Nfor the revelation of the face
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.63,0:14:28.13,Director,,0,0,0,,of this mysterious young woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.05,0:14:33.76,Director,,0,0,0,,We used long shots for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.39,0:14:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid it's the only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.56,0:14:40.73,Director,,0,0,0,,We used long shots,\Nbut we know her in real life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.86,0:14:43.02,Director,,0,0,0,,We know it's Adèle Haenel\Nand we know her face well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.86,0:14:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She has no dresses yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.94,0:14:49.74,Director,,0,0,0,,That green dress is the only\Nconventional dress in the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.82,0:14:51.07,Director,,0,0,0,,It's in the style of Watteau,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.20,0:14:55.04,Director,,0,0,0,,the style people choose\Nwhen they want to recreate that era,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.16,0:14:58.46,Director,,0,0,0,,because it's beautiful\Nand very pictorial, identifiable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.58,0:15:04.13,Director,,0,0,0,,We selected coarser fabrics\Nfor the rest of the costumes:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.25,0:15:07.09,Director,,0,0,0,,cottons and linens\Nmore everyday materials.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.59,0:15:09.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you recognise it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.88,0:15:11.30,Director,,0,0,0,,But with strong colours.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.39,0:15:13.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My father painted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.10,0:15:19.60,Director,,0,0,0,,Here the countess\Narrives on the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.77,0:15:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was in Milan,\Nbefore my marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.65,0:15:24.11,Director,,0,0,0,,Played by Valeria Golino.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.36,0:15:29.61,Director,,0,0,0,,I had Valeria in mind\Nwhen I wrote the screenplay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.78,0:15:32.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My daughter's suitor is Milanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.49,0:15:34.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll go there\Nif he likes the portrait.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.99,0:15:36.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.20,0:15:37.66,Director,,0,0,0,,I wanted it to be Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.75,0:15:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to tell you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.41,0:15:40.87,Director,,0,0,0,,A 50-year-old woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.96,0:15:42.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She wore out one painter before you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.96,0:15:44.34,Director,,0,0,0,,With all that that age promises.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.46,0:15:47.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In a very simple manner,\Nshe refused to pose.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.63,0:15:48.80,Director,,0,0,0,,That physique, that beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.92,0:15:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He never saw her face.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.26,0:15:52.55,Director,,0,0,0,,I didn't want\Na cantankerous old woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.68,0:15:54.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She refuses this marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.30,0:15:55.72,Director,,0,0,0,,That would have been too brutal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.81,0:16:00.56,Director,,0,0,0,,Even though she embodies authority,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.69,0:16:03.56,Director,,0,0,0,,even though it's a relief\Nwhen she disappears...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.69,0:16:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She thinks\Nyou're a companion for walks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.57,0:16:08.11,Director,,0,0,0,,...there is a horizontal relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.19,0:16:09.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.74,0:16:12.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since she arrived,\NI don't let her out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.28,0:16:13.36,Director,,0,0,0,,They speak frankly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.49,0:16:14.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.28,0:16:19.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't wary enough\Nwith her sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.66,0:16:23.54,Director,,0,0,0,,She's like the big boss\Nof a video game.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.67,0:16:25.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She thinks I'll watch over her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.33,0:16:26.50,Director,,0,0,0,,She explains the rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.67,0:16:28.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you observe her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.84,0:16:33.76,Director,,0,0,0,,After this scene\Nthe audience knows what's at stake...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.88,0:16:35.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,More than being a companion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.89,0:16:38.97,Director,,0,0,0,,...and can give itself up\Nto the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.10,0:16:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The portrait arrived here\Nbefore me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.44,0:16:48.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I first entered this room
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.15,0:16:50.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found myself facing my image...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.57,0:16:53.65,Director,,0,0,0,,We set up a very tight storyline\Nwith lots of rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.78,0:16:55.57,Director,,0,0,0,,Now we're going to experience it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.58,0:17:06.54,Director,,0,0,0,,Here we see the character\Ndeliberating over her own set.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.71,0:17:10.09,Director,,0,0,0,,You see the decisions made\Nabout the positioning of the props.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.42,0:17:14.51,Director,,0,0,0,,Chests.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.47,0:17:17.60,Director,,0,0,0,,Made of wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.97,0:17:21.60,Director,,0,0,0,,Nothing ostentatious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.32,0:17:31.03,Director,,0,0,0,,The painter's studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.15,0:17:34.57,Director,,0,0,0,,We did a lot of work on that,\Na lot of research,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.70,0:17:37.49,Director,,0,0,0,,both with the set decorator\Nand with the painter, Hélène Delmaire,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.62,0:17:39.66,Director,,0,0,0,,who stood in for Marianne\Nand created the works.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.46,0:17:55.26,Director,,0,0,0,,{And a new face.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.38,0:17:59.26,Director,,0,0,0,,We stuck to what was customary,\Nthe size of the canvas for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.06,0:18:06.19,Director,,0,0,0,,The various stages needed\Nfor priming the canvas.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.44,0:18:15.32,Director,,0,0,0,,Here comes the rule: The curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.20,0:18:20.12,Director,,0,0,0,,As a boundary and for secrecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.04,0:18:28.12,Director,,0,0,0,,All my films thus far\Nhave been based on secrecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.87,0:18:29.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.00,0:18:32.59,Director,,0,0,0,,Only, this is the first film\Nwhere the secret doesn't last.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.25,0:18:34.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.38,0:18:36.84,Director,,0,0,0,,It's almost a reservoir, a reserve\Nfor what's about to be said.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.97,0:18:38.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did she die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.01,0:18:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were walking by the cliffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.51,0:18:45.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was behind me and vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.35,0:18:48.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw her broken body below.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.69,0:18:52.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Did you see her fall?\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.48,0:18:54.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think she jumped.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.45,0:18:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why do you think that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.03,0:19:03.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She didn't cry out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.58,0:19:10.67,Director,,0,0,0,,This is a really big moment\Nfor the character.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.79,0:19:12.75,Director,,0,0,0,,A bit less so for the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.88,0:19:13.96,Director,,0,0,0,,That's always annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.09,0:19:17.09,Director,,0,0,0,,Because the audience knows\Nwhat Adèle Haenel looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.38,0:19:20.05,Director,,0,0,0,,And it's her we think of.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.18,0:19:22.80,Director,,0,0,0,,So I had to create\Nthe frustration again
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.93,0:19:25.77,Director,,0,0,0,,and the desire to see this face\Nwhich we are already familiar with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.64,0:19:29.77,Director,,0,0,0,,I had to choreograph\Nthe desire to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.02,0:19:33.81,Director,,0,0,0,,How do you reintroduce\Na face to the screen?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.23,0:19:38.61,Director,,0,0,0,,First by hiding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.24,0:19:45.74,Director,,0,0,0,,Then by gradually revealing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.95,0:19:50.04,Director,,0,0,0,,The hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.21,0:19:59.05,Director,,0,0,0,,By approaching it from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.59,0:20:01.26,Director,,0,0,0,,We might see the nape of the neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.43,0:20:05.51,Director,,0,0,0,,And then by changing the focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.64,0:20:06.93,Director,,0,0,0,,By adding danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.39,0:20:12.85,Director,,0,0,0,,A distraction from the face,\Na change of direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.86,0:20:18.28,Director,,0,0,0,,And so, the face appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.19,0:20:20.32,Director,,0,0,0,,As a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.99,0:20:24.70,Director,,0,0,0,,It offers itself up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.82,0:20:25.83,Director,,0,0,0,,She turns round.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.99,0:20:28.54,Director,,0,0,0,,"I've dreamt of that for years."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.00,0:20:32.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dying?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.25,0:20:34.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Running.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.01,0:20:45.09,Director,,0,0,0,,A Breton landscape,\Nthe Côte Sauvage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.93,0:20:48.81,Director,,0,0,0,,It has the advantage\Nof not being at all built-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.47,0:20:52.64,Director,,0,0,0,,Here we relied on nature\Nto recreate the era.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.94,0:20:55.35,Director,,0,0,0,,Or rather to revive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.65,0:21:00.65,Director,,0,0,0,,This scene was written\Ninto the screenplay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.78,0:21:03.99,Director,,0,0,0,,The idea was to look at Héloïse\Nwithout seeing her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.41,0:21:08.58,Director,,0,0,0,,And then she notices\Nthe dark look on her face.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.91,0:21:12.91,Director,,0,0,0,,But we only decided on the staging\Nduring the shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.54,0:21:16.63,Director,,0,0,0,,The idea was for one face\Nto eclipse the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.79,0:21:20.80,Director,,0,0,0,,The choreography was done\Nwith the two actresses there,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.92,0:21:22.80,Director,,0,0,0,,on the spur of the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.92,0:21:26.59,Director,,0,0,0,,At the time I was thinking of Bergman.\NPark Chan-wook springs to mind too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.78,0:21:46.03,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,ADÈLE HAENEL: I constructed the character\Nin three phases.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.16,0:21:49.66,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,I called the first phase,\Nwhich is the one we can see now,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.74,0:21:52.20,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,the Japanese phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.33,0:21:56.96,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,because I had a cape so I saw myself\Nas an intergalactic Japanese emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.75,0:22:03.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Its tone, even in the light,\Nmust yield to the cheek,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.30,0:22:06.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}which is more prominent.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.26,0:22:10.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you bring a book?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.93,0:22:13.35,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,This part of the film\Nis about self-restraint,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.43,0:22:15.23,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,which could be frustrating\Nat the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.35,0:22:19.73,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,But it allowed us to build up\Nthis sort of meta-emotion
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.86,0:22:21.57,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,in the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.69,0:22:23.90,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,So I was very careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.03,0:22:26.28,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,First I had to speak\Nin a higher voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.40,0:22:27.99,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,with a clear diction,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.11,0:22:31.66,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,to convey as little emotion\Nas possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.08,0:22:40.92,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,The attempt to create\Nthis impassive, cold character
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.04,0:22:43.92,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,was also a political attempt\Nat resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.05,0:22:46.72,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,For me it was a way of saying
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.84,0:22:51.05,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,that since this former nun was going\Nto be married against her will,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.18,0:22:53.06,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,without her opinion being sought\Non her own life,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.18,0:22:55.06,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,her only resistance\Nwas through her absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.77,0:22:58.60,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,Only, the truth is,\Nyou can't really absent yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.73,0:23:00.40,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,you can stop yourself from living.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.52,0:23:01.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.15,0:23:04.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's odd you sleep here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.82,0:23:11.45,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,She's in a hybrid state.\NShe's still figuring it all out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.96,0:23:24.17,Director,,0,0,0,,SCIAMMA: The dynamic of secrecy\Nbegins here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.30,0:23:26.51,Director,,0,0,0,,These scenes appear simple,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.63,0:23:28.63,Director,,0,0,0,,but they required\Na huge amount of preparation.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.80,0:23:34.14,Director,,0,0,0,,These sketches of Adèle's face,\Nfor example.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.26,0:23:36.27,Director,,0,0,0,,And especially the light\Nin all the night scenes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.39,0:23:40.48,Director,,0,0,0,,which were cleverly constructed\Nand shot in the middle of the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.60,0:23:42.23,Director,,0,0,0,,and you can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.36,0:23:46.03,Director,,0,0,0,,I love Noémie's face there,\Nlike a child waking up at Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.86,0:23:53.74,Director,,0,0,0,,The first stage is this silhouette,\Nthis bold outline.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.49,0:23:57.75,Director,,0,0,0,,Here we are focussing on the work,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.91,0:24:00.25,Director,,0,0,0,,on the construction of a work,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.37,0:24:02.67,Director,,0,0,0,,showing all the stages,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.83,0:24:04.54,Director,,0,0,0,,and showing them in real time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.17,0:24:10.63,Director,,0,0,0,,We filmed 40 minutes\Nof work at a time,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.76,0:24:15.51,Director,,0,0,0,,knowing we'd only keep\Nthe real-time sequence shots,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.64,0:24:17.22,Director,,0,0,0,,the actual gestures of the painter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.35,0:24:19.27,Director,,0,0,0,,There were very few cuts,\Nvery few cheats.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.02,0:24:24.15,Director,,0,0,0,,Believing in this time of working,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.27,0:24:28.61,Director,,0,0,0,,believing in someone\Nwe see thinking and searching,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.73,0:24:30.19,Director,,0,0,0,,believing in this rhythm.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.12,0:24:36.99,Director,,0,0,0,,This is the wash-drawing stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.16,0:24:43.29,Director,,0,0,0,,We tried to be radical,\Nto bring the face to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.42,0:24:44.71,Director,,0,0,0,,We wanted to be generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.38,0:24:49.67,Director,,0,0,0,,That was done in real time too.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.55,0:24:53.68,Director,,0,0,0,,The work of Noémie Merlant.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.80,0:24:56.85,Director,,0,0,0,,She always watched\Nthe painter paint first,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.97,0:25:00.81,Director,,0,0,0,,not so that she could\Ncopy her gestures
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.93,0:25:03.02,Director,,0,0,0,,but so that she could\Nmake them her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.36,0:25:13.57,Director,,0,0,0,,The way of looking\Nobviously plays a big part.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.41,0:25:22.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miss...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.25,0:25:23.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.46,0:25:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.38,0:25:34.88,Director,,0,0,0,,That choreography again,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.76,0:25:37.51,Director,,0,0,0,,the curtain on both sides,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.35,0:25:39.39,Director,,0,0,0,,the ritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.93,0:25:46.73,Director,,0,0,0,,And the scarf, which is a device\Nwritten into the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.85,0:25:47.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's windy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.90,0:25:52.07,Director,,0,0,0,,The scarf crops up here
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.19,0:25:54.28,Director,,0,0,0,,so that it can feature again\Nin an hour and ten minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.99,0:25:57.41,Director,,0,0,0,,That's how writing works.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.37,0:26:06.96,Director,,0,0,0,,It has the advantage\Nof masking the face
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.04,0:26:08.46,Director,,0,0,0,,that she is meant to be observing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.21,0:26:13.71,Director,,0,0,0,,Sometimes hiding certain things\Nallows us to see others.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.55,0:26:18.89,Director,,0,0,0,,There was the challenge\Nof this long tracking shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.22,0:26:22.22,Director,,0,0,0,,It's a collection of looks\Nby Adèle Haenel.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.78,0:26:37.20,Director,,0,0,0,,And the beach...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.95,0:26:40.78,Director,,0,0,0,,...is portrayed\Nas the end of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.79,0:26:44.91,Director,,0,0,0,,We keep feeling as if she's come\Nto the end of her world.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.29,0:26:47.75,Director,,0,0,0,,Tatooine comes to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.42,0:26:51.09,Director,,0,0,0,,Intergalactic emperors too.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.22,0:27:04.22,Director,,0,0,0,,All these beach scenes were shot\Nduring the first week of filming.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.35,0:27:11.23,Director,,0,0,0,,That was when I discovered\Nwhat the two actresses were capable of.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.27,0:27:14.44,Director,,0,0,0,,Especially...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.44,0:27:18.57,Director,,0,0,0,,Adèle Haenel's very precise work\Nof transformation.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.70,0:27:19.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like to bathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.91,0:27:24.20,Director,,0,0,0,,This was the first scene we shot\Nwhere she speaks,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.37,0:27:26.16,Director,,0,0,0,,when I discovered her voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.37,0:27:28.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On a calmer day.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.46,0:27:31.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.38,0:27:34.75,Director,,0,0,0,,That "yes" is a perfectly timed pause.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.88,0:27:36.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How long will you stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.84,0:27:37.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Six more days.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.97,0:27:40.09,Director,,0,0,0,,It shows how precise\Nthe work we did together was.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.72,0:27:43.43,Director,,0,0,0,,That "yes" always broke my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.89,0:27:45.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you swim?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.77,0:27:51.15,Director,,0,0,0,,The face is revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.27,0:27:52.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.65,0:27:54.73,Director,,0,0,0,,The conversation is\Nabout them looking at one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.90,0:27:56.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's too dangerous if you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.32,0:28:00.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I meant,\NI don't know if can swim.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.24,0:28:07.95,Director,,0,0,0,,Sound work for the waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.08,0:28:11.25,Director,,0,0,0,,The sea is the hardest sound to record\Nbecause it is always a contradiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.37,0:28:14.46,Director,,0,0,0,,If the wave is big,\Nthe sound is ill defined and noisy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.75,0:28:18.96,Director,,0,0,0,,If the wave is small,\Nthe sound is well defined.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.13,0:28:23.05,Director,,0,0,0,,So we used small waves\Nto produce the sound of big waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.80,0:28:28.81,Director,,0,0,0,,The work we did editing the sound\Nwas very precise and very powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.48,0:28:35.40,Director,,0,0,0,,The luminosity and the sunshine\Nweren't written into the screenplay.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.52,0:28:39.40,Director,,0,0,0,,You don't choose Brittany in October\Nfor the sunshine.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.53,0:28:42.49,Director,,0,0,0,,But you have to learn to welcome\Nthe light as good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.70,0:28:52.67,Director,,0,0,0,,The director of photography and I\Nwere happy about the luminosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.79,0:28:54.63,Director,,0,0,0,,We decided it suited the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.71,0:28:56.75,Director,,0,0,0,,We brought it back from Brittany and...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.88,0:28:57.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How was your day?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.00,0:29:02.26,Director,,0,0,0,,And then we incorporated it\Ninto our choices about lighting
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.38,0:29:03.38,Director,,0,0,0,,throughout the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.80,0:29:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She always stays ahead of me\Nand walks alone on the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.85,0:29:13.64,Director,,0,0,0,,Here, what's important\Nis that the character is drinking beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.85,0:29:16.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you started painting?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.77,0:29:19.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.40,0:29:22.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't even seen her smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.95,0:29:25.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you tried to be funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.75,0:29:40.25,Director,,0,0,0,,The palette was a prop\Nthat terrified me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.34,0:29:45.97,Director,,0,0,0,,It was purpose-built,\Nlike so many of the props in the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.68,0:29:55.52,Director,,0,0,0,,Here she's working on the image,\Non the painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.64,0:29:59.19,Director,,0,0,0,,We decided to film it\Nin very high definition
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.32,0:30:01.82,Director,,0,0,0,,to get the effects of the materials
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.94,0:30:03.36,Director,,0,0,0,,to provide a lot of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.03,0:30:08.28,Director,,0,0,0,,And then there's the sound editing,\Nsound effects too.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.53,0:30:11.54,Director,,0,0,0,,We worked on...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.25,0:30:14.62,Director,,0,0,0,,...the wetness...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.62,0:30:16.75,Director,,0,0,0,,...and the touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.71,0:30:19.17,Director,,0,0,0,,It was very precise work.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.61,0:30:41.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it unfinished?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.32,0:30:44.11,Director,,0,0,0,,This was the first real exchange\Nbetween the two characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.24,0:30:47.57,Director,,0,0,0,,Directing it was a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.70,0:30:48.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think she wanted to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.12,0:30:51.74,Director,,0,0,0,,Filming a sequence shot\Nby the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.66,0:30:56.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the first person\Nunafraid to ask that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.54,0:30:57.92,Director,,0,0,0,,It's a long scene. It was hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.04,0:30:59.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apart from you?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.83,0:31:01.71,Director,,0,0,0,,We did lots of takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.84,0:31:03.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not out loud. But yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.55,0:31:08.80,Director,,0,0,0,,We finally decided to do close-ups\Non each of the two actresses.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.93,0:31:11.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In her last letter, she apologised.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.26,0:31:12.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For no reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.39,0:31:15.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What could she be apologising for?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.27,0:31:19.90,Director,,0,0,0,,After their respective close-ups,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.02,0:31:22.31,Director,,0,0,0,,we decided to do a take\Nthat was a sequence shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.98,0:31:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You make it sound terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.78,0:31:27.95,Director,,0,0,0,,Just one, and it was this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.37,0:31:33.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you know\Nof my marriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.70,0:31:38.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're to wed\Na Milanese gentleman, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.12,0:31:42.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all I know, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.29,0:31:44.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You see why it worries me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.21,0:31:48.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Put that way, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.01,0:31:51.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I put it the way it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.01,0:31:57.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd rather have stayed\Nin the convent?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.60,0:31:59.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a life that has advantages.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.06,0:32:01.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a library.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.60,0:32:03.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can sing or hear music.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.07,0:32:11.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And equality is a pleasant feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.61,0:32:15.12,Director,,0,0,0,,"Equality is a pleasant feeling."\NOne of the key lines in the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.99,0:32:18.91,Director,,0,0,0,,A line that is key to the dynamic\Nbetween them, to their relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.00,0:32:21.37,Director,,0,0,0,,And key to the screenplay,\Nbecause this film was an attempt
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.50,0:32:24.04,Director,,0,0,0,,to write a love story\Nbased on equality.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.17,0:32:25.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You draw?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.50,0:32:28.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. A little.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.47,0:32:32.72,Director,,0,0,0,,A story about an artistic collaboration\Nbased on equality
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.84,0:32:36.97,Director,,0,0,0,,and a screenplay which is not based\Non a dynamic of conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.10,0:32:39.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about you?\NWhen will you marry?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.39,0:32:42.77,Director,,0,0,0,,All the possible narratives in it,\Nall the possible emotions too.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.90,0:32:45.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.27,0:32:47.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- You don't have to?\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.65,0:32:51.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll take over my father's business.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.57,0:32:53.95,Director,,0,0,0,,What we were thinking in 2018\Nwhen we were making the film
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.07,0:32:56.03,Director,,0,0,0,,is what this character\Nwas thinking in 1770.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.74,0:33:00.87,Director,,0,0,0,,She helps us to think it today.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.91,0:33:05.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can choose.\NThat's why you don't understand me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.59,0:33:11.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.26,0:33:16.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How are your days?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.89,0:33:19.93,Director,,0,0,0,,We return late\Nand l have little light to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.64,0:33:23.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll keep her here\Ntomorrow afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.98,0:33:26.48,Director,,0,0,0,,The work we did with Valeria Golino\Nwas very specific
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.61,0:33:28.69,Director,,0,0,0,,because she arrived\Nat the end of the shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.82,0:33:31.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you could allow her\Nto go out alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.24,0:33:34.66,Director,,0,0,0,,She was only there for three days\Nand she had all these scenes...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.78,0:33:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She isn't sad, but angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.57,0:33:38.66,Director,,0,0,0,,...peppered throughout the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.78,0:33:40.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think I don't know her anger?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.91,0:33:45.08,Director,,0,0,0,,I chose Valeria\Nfor her childlike qualities, her joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.21,0:33:46.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I know it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.71,0:33:48.00,Director,,0,0,0,,Which are then taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.05,0:33:51.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where did you learn Italian?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.38,0:33:54.26,Director,,0,0,0,,She said she was scared\Nof being directed by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.38,0:33:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know Milan?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.22,0:33:58.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.68,0:34:00.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's twenty years\Nsince I was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.72,0:34:01.72,Director,,0,0,0,,And I believe her.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.85,0:34:03.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell her Milan is beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.48,0:34:06.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that life will be sweeter.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.36,0:34:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She doesn't talk much to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.36,0:34:13.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not marrying her\Nto the local gentry.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.57,0:34:15.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm trying\Nto take her elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.99,0:34:17.24,Director,,0,0,0,,Here comes the melancholy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.37,0:34:19.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She'll be less bored there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.16,0:34:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.70,0:34:23.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed. Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.87,0:34:30.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll leave for the coast\Nat the same time as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.54,0:34:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you don't have\Nto return to Paris,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.84,0:34:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,l have a friend\Nwho'd like her portrait done.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.59,0:34:38.76,Director,,0,0,0,,This is the climax of the alliance\Nbetween the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.89,0:34:42.81,Director,,0,0,0,,It's a classic storyline,\Nwoven at the start,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.93,0:34:45.85,Director,,0,0,0,,a story about complicity\Nand secrecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.60,0:34:50.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's very ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.56,0:34:52.15,Director,,0,0,0,,The promise of a career, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.61,0:34:57.07,Director,,0,0,0,,But the story soon departs from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.24,0:34:59.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've made me laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.70,0:35:01.70,Director,,0,0,0,,It's a red herring,\Neven for the characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.83,0:35:03.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's ages since that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.00,0:35:06.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.50,0:35:09.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.25,0:35:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It takes two to be funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.42,0:35:17.84,Director,,0,0,0,,The face is finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.10,0:35:23.72,Director,,0,0,0,,It's time to move onto the dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.14,0:35:28.27,Director,,0,0,0,,And this is when the absence\Nof the model is starting to be felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.94,0:35:34.28,Director,,0,0,0,,There is a theory\Namong art historians
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.40,0:35:36.57,Director,,0,0,0,,that women invented self-portraiture.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.74,0:35:39.82,Director,,0,0,0,,Perhaps because\Nthey didn't have models.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.32,0:35:42.95,Director,,0,0,0,,So they had to paint themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.04,0:35:46.95,Director,,0,0,0,,This dress is worn\Nby all three characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.79,0:35:50.96,Director,,0,0,0,,First... Marianne.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.26,0:35:58.30,Director,,0,0,0,,Playing with mirrors.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.93,0:36:01.26,Director,,0,0,0,,The head is cutoff.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.43,0:36:04.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Marianne?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.64,0:36:08.60,Director,,0,0,0,,All the elements in the shot contribute\Nto the dramatic composition.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.73,0:36:10.73,Director,,0,0,0,,The mirror, the chair, the curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.69,0:36:17.53,Director,,0,0,0,,Here comes Darth Vader.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.21,0:36:35.42,Director,,0,0,0,,And the image she's dreamt of,\Nthat of the model.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.92,0:36:40.59,Director,,0,0,0,,The desire for a reverse angle shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.51,0:36:44.30,Director,,0,0,0,,It doesn't last long enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.81,0:36:50.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have tobacco?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.56,0:36:53.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.69,0:36:56.94,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,HAENEL: This scene was\Nin the second phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.07,0:36:59.40,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,the most hybrid phase: The thaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.82,0:37:05.07,Director,,0,0,0,,SCIAMMA: The first deliberately intimate scene\Nbetween the two characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.87,0:37:08.29,Director,,0,0,0,,And a sequence shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.16,0:37:14.38,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,HAENEL: The challenge here was to introduce\Nsome cracks in the mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.17,0:37:18.25,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,The face starting to soften.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.76,0:37:23.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your mother will let you\Ngo out alone tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.72,0:37:26.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll be free.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.81,0:37:30.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being free is being alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.39,0:37:32.60,Director,,0,0,0,,SCIAMMA: The first scene of intimacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.77,0:37:33.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.89,0:37:37.15,Director,,0,0,0,,The first time they're confronted\Nwith how the other one thinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.27,0:37:40.61,Director,,0,0,0,,And here Héloïse thinks like Héloïse.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.74,0:37:44.32,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,HAENEL: There's an element of self-control,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.45,0:37:46.91,Director,,0,0,0,,but it's more candid\Nthan at the start
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.03,0:37:50.20,Director,,0,0,0,,with a sort of emotionalism\Nstarting to break through.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.33,0:37:52.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Organ music is pretty but bleak.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.79,0:37:54.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.42,0:37:57.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've never heard an orchestra?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.88,0:38:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.51,0:38:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.85,0:38:13.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not easy to relate music.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.90,0:38:24.45,Director,,0,0,0,,SCIAMMA: Another sequence shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.95,0:38:35.54,Director,,0,0,0,,Noémie Merlant was enthusiastic\Nabout learning to play the spinette,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.71,0:38:37.71,Director,,0,0,0,,which is this little harpsichord,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.83,0:38:39.92,Director,,0,0,0,,and she spent weeks on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.75,0:38:43.34,Director,,0,0,0,,She does actually play it here\Nbut under a sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.43,0:38:50.30,Director,,0,0,0,,A reinterpretation of Vivaldi.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.64,0:38:54.68,Director,,0,0,0,,We picked\Na well-known classical piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.23,0:38:58.60,Director,,0,0,0,,For its democratic virtues.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.44,0:39:03.57,Director,,0,0,0,,It's identifiable from the first notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.69,0:39:05.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.90,0:39:07.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A piece that I love.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.16,0:39:14.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it merry?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.29,0:39:18.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not merry, but it's lively.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.56,0:39:33.85,Director,,0,0,0,,Vivaldi's "Four Seasons".
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.97,0:39:35.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's about a coming storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.02,0:39:41.52,Director,,0,0,0,,Accompanied by poems he wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.69,0:39:43.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The insects sense it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.86,0:39:48.11,Director,,0,0,0,,Marianne's interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.28,0:39:49.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They become agitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.82,0:39:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the storm breaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.53,0:39:53.74,Director,,0,0,0,,Her interpretation of the poem.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.87,0:39:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With lightning and the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.46,0:40:05.17,Director,,0,0,0,,The first time the fire appears\Nbetween the characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.63,0:40:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't remember it...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.38,0:40:14.56,Director,,0,0,0,,This time it's Marianne who's burning\Nwith Héloïse watching her.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.68,0:40:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll hear the rest.\NMilan is a city of music.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.35,0:40:20.10,Director,,0,0,0,,Maybe the one looking\Nmakes the other one burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.27,0:40:23.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I can't wait for Milan.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.57,0:40:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm saying there will be good things.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.78,0:40:37.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying that, now and then,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.33,0:40:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be consoled.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.89,0:40:56.39,Director,,0,0,0,,The guilt associated with secrecy\Nis at play here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.06,0:41:08.48,Director,,0,0,0,,For the first time,\Nthe eyes darting back and forth
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.61,0:41:10.44,Director,,0,0,0,,between the canvas and a model,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.57,0:41:13.57,Director,,0,0,0,,even though\Nshe's still painting in secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.66,0:41:20.20,Director,,0,0,0,,A desire to see a reverse angle shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.21,0:41:22.54,Director,,0,0,0,,But we take our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.26,0:41:37.56,Director,,0,0,0,,Working on the image,\Nrecreating the colour and the material.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.10,0:41:46.56,Director,,0,0,0,,And still choosing to show the work\Nof the painter in real time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.03,0:41:59.33,Director,,0,0,0,,The second character\Nin the green dress: Sophie.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.25,0:42:07.71,Director,,0,0,0,,This scene is one\Nthat we had dreamt of,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.84,0:42:12.55,Director,,0,0,0,,one we felt strongly about,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.67,0:42:14.80,Director,,0,0,0,,without knowing\Nwhat place it would occupy
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.93,0:42:17.01,Director,,0,0,0,,simply knowing it would be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.14,0:42:21.02,Director,,0,0,0,,A sequence shot with a conjuring trick:\NThe retraction of her hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.64,0:42:26.06,Director,,0,0,0,,Minutely choreographed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.19,0:42:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How was mass?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.11,0:42:30.61,Director,,0,0,0,,Again resting on\Nthe actresses' ideas and physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.73,0:42:32.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You look cheerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.44,0:42:33.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I sang a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.03,0:42:36.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you leaving me already?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.86,0:42:38.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.28,0:42:40.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you come out tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.70,0:42:44.79,Director,,0,0,0,,Added to the secrecy,\Nthe admission of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.83,0:42:47.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In solitude,\NI felt the liberty you spoke of.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.34,0:42:51.55,Director,,0,0,0,,A meeting of minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.67,0:42:53.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I also felt your absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.27,0:43:14.69,Director,,0,0,0,,The painting is finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.82,0:43:17.74,Director,,0,0,0,,It is not placed in the centre\Nof the frame like a work of art.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.86,0:43:21.41,Director,,0,0,0,,It is kept in the background\Nand it's blurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.08,0:43:27.75,Director,,0,0,0,,It's the work's vocation that counts.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.75,0:43:30.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The portrait is finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.71,0:43:34.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you happy with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.34,0:43:37.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.72,0:43:41.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go and see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.89,0:43:45.77,Director,,0,0,0,,When a story revolves\Naround a secret,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.89,0:43:49.06,Director,,0,0,0,,the real challenge\Nis the timing of the revelation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.19,0:43:50.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I ask a favour?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.65,0:43:54.65,Director,,0,0,0,,There are films which depend\Non the final revelation of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.78,0:43:55.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.90,0:44:00.03,Director,,0,0,0,,But here the character chooses\Nto reveal it, demanding to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.16,0:44:02.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like to show her first.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.04,0:44:06.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And tell her the truth myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.33,0:44:09.83,Director,,0,0,0,,This is where it diverts\Nfrom most stories about a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.00,0:44:11.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.54,0:44:13.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's very fond of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.92,0:44:18.92,Director,,0,0,0,,There's an attempt\Nto resolve the conflict in a different way.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.30,0:44:18.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.18,0:44:24.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an8}She talks about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.56,0:44:33.40,Director,,0,0,0,,We had to include\Na vague feeling of guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.69,0:44:38.32,Director,,0,0,0,,It was a way\Nof building the momentum.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.99,0:44:49.37,Director,,0,0,0,,Making room\Nfor the sound of the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.41,0:44:53.75,Director,,0,0,0,,It plays a very precise role\Nin the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.38,0:44:59.42,Director,,0,0,0,,When is the fire part of the picture?\NWhen is it part of the soundtrack?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.55,0:45:03.22,Director,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's visual and not audible.\NOther times it's audible and not visual.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.30,0:45:04.97,Director,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it doesn't figure at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.18,0:45:09.10,Director,,0,0,0,,There was a catalogue of fires\Nin the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.06,0:45:13.90,Director,,0,0,0,,It was a challenge as well as a pleasure\Nfor the director of photography.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.74,0:45:23.07,Director,,0,0,0,,At this turning point in the film,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.24,0:45:25.74,Director,,0,0,0,,the conventional storyline\Nhas a new angle.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.74,0:45:29.16,Director,,0,0,0,,There is...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.41,0:45:32.54,Director,,0,0,0,,...this image,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.54,0:45:35.88,Director,,0,0,0,,this literal image...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.46,0:45:38.63,Director,,0,0,0,,...of a heart set alight.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.76,0:45:43.13,Director,,0,0,0,,There is a certain naivety.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.39,0:45:52.35,Director,,0,0,0,,These are camera effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.98,0:45:56.77,Director,,0,0,0,,There is a return\Nto a primitive language.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.48,0:46:02.86,Director,,0,0,0,,But the primitive language\Nis inevitably a new language.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.18,0:46:26.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I must tell you something.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.31,0:46:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a painter.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.43,0:46:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came here to paint you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.85,0:46:38.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I finished your portrait last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.40,0:46:45.78,Director,,0,0,0,,The dynamic of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.91,0:46:47.95,Director,,0,0,0,,Curiously, in the truth,\Nin the absence of lies...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.07,0:46:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see now why you praised\Nthe charms of exile.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.53,0:46:52.12,Director,,0,0,0,,...lies the possibility of invention.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.24,0:46:54.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You felt guilty.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.12,0:46:57.08,Director,,0,0,0,,Or at least of surprise,\Nfor the story and for the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.38,0:47:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.93,0:47:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later today. With your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.89,0:47:12.52,Director,,0,0,0,,If we can say anything at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.18,0:47:16.60,Director,,0,0,0,,...what do we say?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.94,0:47:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I shall bathe today.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.11,0:47:30.16,Director,,0,0,0,,Héloïse decides\Nto expand her world
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.28,0:47:32.83,Director,,0,0,0,,because her world\Nhas come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.12,0:47:36.37,Director,,0,0,0,,It's October.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.42,0:47:41.17,Director,,0,0,0,,It's Brittany.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.29,0:47:43.50,Director,,0,0,0,,So it's one take, just one.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.04,0:48:24.46,Director,,0,0,0,,The next sequence\Nwas filmed straight after the swim,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.21,0:48:27.63,Director,,0,0,0,,so the cold is real.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.22,0:48:39.64,Director,,0,0,0,,Their separation is imminent,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.48,0:48:43.06,Director,,0,0,0,,but Héloïse hasn't reacted.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.19,0:48:44.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, can you swim?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.02,0:48:46.07,Director,,0,0,0,,We are waiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.19,0:48:47.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still don't know if can.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.57,0:48:48.86,Director,,0,0,0,,...for her to show her feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.99,0:48:50.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.32,0:48:52.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can float.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.24,0:48:55.91,Director,,0,0,0,,The film makes us wait
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.04,0:48:57.24,Director,,0,0,0,,for the conflict,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.20,0:49:01.75,Director,,0,0,0,,by not revealing everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.21,0:49:03.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.33,0:49:04.42,Director,,0,0,0,,...too rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.55,0:49:10.59,Director,,0,0,0,,The characters take their time to reflect.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.59,0:49:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It explains all your looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.01,0:49:17.47,Director,,0,0,0,,Here the love is apparent\Nand yet denied.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.02,0:49:22.19,Director,,0,0,0,,It wasn't love.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.28,0:49:35.57,Director,,0,0,0,,I remember this sequence.\NIt was number 30.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.70,0:49:39.45,Director,,0,0,0,,If you remember the number\Nit's because it was a pivotal sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.58,0:49:41.87,Director,,0,0,0,,This is the moment\Nthe language of the film changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.46,0:49:43.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.63,0:49:49.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that me?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.76,0:49:52.17,Director,,0,0,0,,Of all the possible reactions\Nfrom the character...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.30,0:49:53.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.43,0:49:56.18,Director,,0,0,0,,...I think\Nher being critical of the work...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.30,0:49:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that how you see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.51,0:49:58.89,Director,,0,0,0,,...is the least expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.39,0:50:03.02,Director,,0,0,0,,It's the start of...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.14,0:50:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not only me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.48,0:50:06.31,Director,,0,0,0,,...a new dynamic\Nbetween the characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.44,0:50:07.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, not only you?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.94,0:50:10.82,Director,,0,0,0,,Now that things are out in the open...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.94,0:50:14.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are rules, conventions, ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.45,0:50:15.95,Director,,0,0,0,,...everyone has an opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.16,0:50:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean there is no life?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.33,0:50:24.00,Director,,0,0,0,,The dialogue is...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.75,0:50:27.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your presence is made up\Nof fleeting moments
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.46,0:50:29.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that may lack truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.21,0:50:30.21,Director,,0,0,0,,...intellectual...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.51,0:50:32.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not everything is fleeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.97,0:50:34.05,Director,,0,0,0,,...critical...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.68,0:50:37.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some feelings are deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.18,0:50:40.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...full of feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.02,0:50:44.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact it isn't close to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.81,0:50:46.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that I can understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.19,0:50:49.27,Director,,0,0,0,,Straightaway the notion\Nof the eye of the beholder.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.40,0:50:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I find it sad\Nit isn't close to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.15,0:50:56.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you know\Nit isn't close to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.07,0:51:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't know you were an art critic.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.99,0:51:03.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't know you were a painter.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.29,0:51:07.75,Director,,0,0,0,,A new chapter.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.46,0:51:10.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll fetch my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.92,0:51:16.43,Director,,0,0,0,,Adèle Haenel walked so stridently\Nthat the camera shook.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.12,0:51:47.42,Director,,0,0,0,,This was at the end of the shoot\Non a film about two self-sufficient women
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.58,0:51:50.50,Director,,0,0,0,,and suddenly,\Nbecause of the order we did it in,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.58,0:51:55.01,Director,,0,0,0,,authority returns to the frame\Nand we had to film three characters.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.13,0:51:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't good enough.\NI'll start again.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.88,0:52:04.31,Director,,0,0,0,,I think all of us on set\Nwere terror-stricken
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.43,0:52:05.52,Director,,0,0,0,,when the time came to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.64,0:52:09.35,Director,,0,0,0,,because suddenly\Nit was the end of our idyll,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.48,0:52:12.23,Director,,0,0,0,,the idyll between these two characters\Nand what it meant...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.36,0:52:13.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's staying.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.48,0:52:15.74,Director,,0,0,0,,...to only have two characters\Nin the frame.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.57,0:52:18.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll pose for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.49,0:52:21.28,Director,,0,0,0,,Suddenly we had\Nto incorporate three.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.87,0:52:23.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.99,0:52:28.71,Director,,0,0,0,,This is really the only decision\NHéloïse takes in the film,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.83,0:52:32.17,Director,,0,0,0,,the only decision about her fate,\Nand it's to pose.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.34,0:52:34.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.92,0:52:38.55,Director,,0,0,0,,The mother and daughter are...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.67,0:52:39.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does it change for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.88,0:52:42.51,Director,,0,0,0,,...genetically quite far-removed\Nfrom one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.64,0:52:45.06,Director,,0,0,0,,but there is the authority\Nof the frame and the profile.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.18,0:52:46.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.02,0:52:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be away for five days.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.77,0:52:55.82,Director,,0,0,0,,How to show\Nin a gesture in the present
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.94,0:52:57.61,Director,,0,0,0,,a past intimacy,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.74,0:52:59.40,Director,,0,0,0,,an intimacy between\Na mother and child.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.53,0:53:00.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.95,0:53:06.62,Director,,0,0,0,,There is the idea\Nof the invention of this kiss...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.70,0:53:08.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say goodbye\Nlike when you were little.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.70,0:53:10.96,Director,,0,0,0,,...which is already unusual,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.12,0:53:13.00,Director,,0,0,0,,but then it was played\Nby Adèle Haenel
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.13,0:53:15.54,Director,,0,0,0,,as if it was something she'd made up\Non the spur of the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.67,0:53:20.51,Director,,0,0,0,,Perhaps for something\Nto belong to two people
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.63,0:53:23.76,Director,,0,0,0,,it must be... new.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.27,0:53:33.60,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,NOÉMIE MERLANT: I spent a lot of time\Nobserving Hélène Delmaire
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.73,0:53:36.98,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,who painted the various paintings\Nyou see in the film
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.11,0:53:39.65,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,and I spent time observing her\Nto try to find Marianne
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.82,0:53:42.41,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,and her relationship\Nwith her work, with painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.20,0:53:45.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.91,0:53:51.41,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,In the first instance I tried to capture\Nher gaze, the painter's gaze,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.54,0:53:53.50,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,which is very specific,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.67,0:53:56.88,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,a mixture of concentration...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.96,0:53:58.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Turn your chest towards me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.25,0:54:00.84,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,...and magic, a gaze...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.97,0:54:01.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A little more.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.09,0:54:06.14,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,...which is piercing\Nbut also distant.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.26,0:54:08.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Turn your head slightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.31,0:54:11.98,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,Then I tried to find my own dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.10,0:54:16.19,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,When I say dance,\NI mean the dance of the painter.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.73,0:54:20.32,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,I worked on the gestures,\Nthe fluidity of the gestures.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.11,0:54:22.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rest your arm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.86,0:54:27.28,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,The relationship and the rhythm\Nof the model and the painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.37,0:54:30.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.91,0:54:33.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.46,0:54:37.42,Director,,0,0,0,,SCIAMMA: The film finally reveals its centrepiece,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.50,0:54:41.59,Director,,0,0,0,,the thing it set out to do,\Nthe thing that inspired it,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.67,0:54:45.76,Director,,0,0,0,,the shot reverse shot\Nof the model and painter.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.89,0:54:48.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Are you comfortable?\N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.43,0:54:50.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you hold this position?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.51,0:54:51.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.56,0:54:58.11,Director,,0,0,0,,The film plays on the paradox\Nthat it's the painter who says...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.23,0:54:59.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.65,0:55:03.65,Director,,0,0,0,,And here it decides\Nto film the desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.90,0:55:05.99,Director,,0,0,0,,The desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.86,0:55:08.66,Director,,0,0,0,,The materiality of desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.70,0:55:11.37,Director,,0,0,0,,The turmoil.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.45,0:55:13.12,Director,,0,0,0,,That gut-wrenching feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.79,0:55:18.63,Director,,0,0,0,,Using the cinema to film desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.21,0:55:21.25,Director,,0,0,0,,Before the lovemaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.11,0:55:47.20,Director,,0,0,0,,Seemingly a continuation of the turmoil\Nbut actually something far more physical.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.32,0:55:49.82,Director,,0,0,0,,Even though, for now,\Nit remains a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.62,0:55:58.00,Director,,0,0,0,,The character is suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.25,0:56:02.63,Director,,0,0,0,,Because she has her period.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.30,0:56:06.63,Director,,0,0,0,,That's something we rarely see\Nin the cinema.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.64,0:56:16.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The heat will do you good.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.27,0:56:19.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cherrystones hold it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.69,0:56:25.65,Director,,0,0,0,,The return of Sophie\Nwho hasn't been seen for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.78,0:56:28.57,Director,,0,0,0,,She has returned\Nbecause she has a reason to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.74,0:56:31.87,Director,,0,0,0,,Now it's her turn\Nto become a main character.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.87,0:56:34.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.87,0:56:42.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I usually have one ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.54,0:56:44.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I haven't had my monthlies.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.13,0:56:49.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,More than once?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.30,0:56:51.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three times.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.01,0:56:56.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this the first time?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.97,0:56:58.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.94,0:57:02.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you want a child?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.19,0:57:07.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was waiting for Madam to leave\Nto see to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.24,0:57:12.45,Director,,0,0,0,,A new territory,\Na world without Madam.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.78,0:57:15.28,Director,,0,0,0,,A world with three of them in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.51,0:57:33.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- I can't.\N- A little more.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.91,0:57:54.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.29,0:58:06.13,Director,,0,0,0,,We named this shot after Miyazaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.92,0:58:11.38,Director,,0,0,0,,A playful shot with appearances\Nand disappearances.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.88,0:58:15.59,Director,,0,0,0,,I don't know why\Nwe thought of {\i0}Totoro{\i1}.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.28,0:58:37.91,Director,,0,0,0,,They're looking for a plant\Nthat will abort, namely rue.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.91,0:58:41.33,Director,,0,0,0,,Hence the expression,\N{\i0}"Un enfant de la rue"{\i1},
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.41,0:58:44.04,Director,,0,0,0,,which doesn't mean\Na child brought up in the street
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.21,0:58:47.33,Director,,0,0,0,,but a child who survived\Nthe plant, the rue,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.46,0:58:48.54,Director,,0,0,0,,which is abortive.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.42,0:58:56.39,Director,,0,0,0,,We're back in the kitchen here\Nfor this difficult sequence
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.51,0:58:58.18,Director,,0,0,0,,which combines two challenges:
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.14,0:59:01.39,Director,,0,0,0,,The dialogue between lovers
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.52,0:59:04.48,Director,,0,0,0,,and a medical,\Nalmost acrobatic, challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.60,0:59:06.31,Director,,0,0,0,,We made a decision...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.48,0:59:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.65,0:59:09.98,Director,,0,0,0,,...on set to film a sequence shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.40,0:59:20.41,Director,,0,0,0,,I always envisaged this kitchen\Nas a domestic space,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.53,0:59:22.95,Director,,0,0,0,,like other domestic spaces\Nin the cinema,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.08,0:59:28.71,Director,,0,0,0,,in Chantal Akerman's {\i0}Jeanne Dielman{\i1},\Nfor example, which I like a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.67,0:59:32.13,Director,,0,0,0,,It was a space which gave us\Nthe courage to film a sequence shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.09,0:59:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will it be enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.55,0:59:35.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll see.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.78,1:00:03.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has it happened to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.58,1:00:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.38,1:00:14.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've known love.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.43,1:00:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.97,1:00:22.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it like?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.93,1:00:26.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's hard to say.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.10,1:00:29.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean, how does it feel?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.42,1:00:59.63,Director,,0,0,0,,This, for example, was\Nan extremely complicated shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.76,1:01:02.43,Director,,0,0,0,,It took four or five hours to shoot.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.18,1:01:06.52,Director,,0,0,0,,A sequence shot\Nlasting two minutes 45 seconds,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.39,1:01:13.23,Director,,0,0,0,,with multiple light sources,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.36,1:01:14.57,Director,,0,0,0,,movement,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.28,1:01:23.45,Director,,0,0,0,,and a tension\Nthat comes from discretion.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.06,1:01:47.93,Director,,0,0,0,,Another example\Nof the decision made...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.35,1:01:51.56,Director,,0,0,0,,...to film at night.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.23,1:02:02.36,Director,,0,0,0,,With a combination of candlelight\Nand natural light.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.07,1:02:07.45,Director,,0,0,0,,You see all the precision\Nin the colours.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.58,1:02:08.91,Director,,0,0,0,,The work of Claire Mathon.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.87,1:02:17.17,Director,,0,0,0,,Candles are the biggest challenge\Nof the reconstruction.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.59,1:02:22.13,Director,,0,0,0,,Are they in the frame?\NAre they on candelabras?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.26,1:02:24.64,Director,,0,0,0,,Are they big or small?\NAre they ostentatious?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.76,1:02:26.85,Director,,0,0,0,,We went for an Arte Povera style.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.97,1:02:30.14,Director,,0,0,0,,Candle ends on planks of wood.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.27,1:02:33.69,Director,,0,0,0,,They tie in with the sociology\Nthat we're seeing,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.85,1:02:36.94,Director,,0,0,0,,even if it's an anachronism\Nto talk about sociology
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.06,1:02:39.73,Director,,0,0,0,,in relation\Nto this Breton aristocracy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.86,1:02:41.78,Director,,0,0,0,,Every candle end\Nis worth something.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.74,1:02:49.12,Director,,0,0,0,,There are flames running\Nthrough every scene in the film.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.24,1:02:53.96,Director,,0,0,0,,The challenge was to never be reliant\Non being able to control them.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.01,1:03:08.43,Director,,0,0,0,,The clandestine behaviour continues\Neven though the secret is out.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.32,1:03:26.03,Director,,0,0,0,,An opportune moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.20,1:03:29.41,Director,,0,0,0,,This scene really hinges,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.53,1:03:32.45,Director,,0,0,0,,after all that tension\Nof the sequence shot,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.58,1:03:34.58,Director,,0,0,0,,on the change of pace.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.00,1:03:39.71,Director,,0,0,0,,And on Adèle Haenel's languor.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.67,1:03:42.67,Director,,0,0,0,,Her opening up.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.77,1:03:57.60,Director,,0,0,0,,This type of sequence relies heavily\Non precision on all levels,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.73,1:04:01.19,Director,,0,0,0,,the precision of the drawing\Nand the subtlety of the actresses
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.94,1:04:04.36,Director,,0,0,0,,and this sound,\Nreinforced by sound effects.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.08,1:04:16.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't make you smile.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.37,1:04:17.58,Director,,0,0,0,,This scene...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.67,1:04:20.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel I do it\Nand then it vanishes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.29,1:04:23.13,Director,,0,0,0,,It's as if it had already taken place\Nbefore we shot it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.34,1:04:26.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anger always comes to the fore.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.72,1:04:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Definitely with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.80,1:04:30.93,Director,,0,0,0,,First, because it's a pivotal scene,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.05,1:04:33.14,Director,,0,0,0,,it's the scene that epitomises...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.26,1:04:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't mean to hurt you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.43,1:04:35.98,Director,,0,0,0,,...the shot reverse shot dynamic.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.10,1:04:37.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You haven't hurt me.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.69,1:04:39.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have, I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.23,1:04:41.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you're moved,\Nyou do this with your hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.06,1:04:45.07,Director,,0,0,0,,What power does the beholder have?\NWho is looking at whom?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.19,1:04:49.36,Director,,0,0,0,,And it's also the scene\Nwe used for the auditions.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.49,1:04:50.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when you're embarrassed...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.91,1:04:52.07,Director,,0,0,0,,For the role of Marianne,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.20,1:04:54.62,Director,,0,0,0,,because Adèle Haenel
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.70,1:04:56.58,Director,,0,0,0,,was already on board.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.96,1:05:01.71,Director,,0,0,0,,When we did the auditions,\NI played the model
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.83,1:05:05.13,Director,,0,0,0,,and the actresses\Nplayed the painter,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.25,1:05:07.80,Director,,0,0,0,,which was somewhat carnivalesque.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.92,1:05:09.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forgive me,\NI'd hate to be in your place.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.84,1:05:12.43,Director,,0,0,0,,It's very hard to shoot scenes\Nyou've used in casting sessions.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.55,1:05:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're in the same place.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.10,1:05:16.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly the same place.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.60,1:05:18.48,Director,,0,0,0,,This scene is all about the editing.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.60,1:05:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.77,1:05:24.57,Director,,0,0,0,,It's about how you leave your shot\Nto enter the reverse shot,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.69,1:05:31.16,Director,,0,0,0,,the other person's shot,\Nwhich is defined by our viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.45,1:05:33.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Step closer.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.50,1:05:41.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.12,1:05:44.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To start with, this scene...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.84,1:05:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you look at me,\Nwho do I look at?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.13,1:05:51.88,Director,,0,0,0,,...showing a shift of power,\Nor an understanding that it's shared,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.01,1:05:55.26,Director,,0,0,0,,was the scene of the first kiss.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.39,1:05:56.89,Director,,0,0,0,,It seemed obvious.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.02,1:06:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you lose control,\Nyou raise your eyebrows.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.36,1:06:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when you're troubled,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.16,1:06:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you breathe through your mouth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.83,1:06:19.25,Director,,0,0,0,,Before I had her saying,\N"You knew I was in turmoil."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.37,1:06:20.37,Director,,0,0,0,,And she replied, "Yes."
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.79,1:06:23.12,Director,,0,0,0,,And they kissed.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.30,1:06:30.72,Director,,0,0,0,,But we decided to take it further.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.59,1:06:38.56,Director,,0,0,0,,This is the only time\Nwe have Marianne framed like this,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.68,1:06:42.18,Director,,0,0,0,,observed, in her fragile state,\Nby the model.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.86,1:06:53.95,Director,,0,0,0,,The only improvised scene\Nin the film.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.07,1:06:59.04,Director,,0,0,0,,A card game,\Nan 18th-century form of Spit.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.16,1:07:01.66,Director,,0,0,0,,It's an extremely authoritative set-up.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.79,1:07:04.00,Director,,0,0,0,,There is this panoramic shot\Nlinking the three characters
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.08,1:07:05.71,Director,,0,0,0,,which sets the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.79,1:07:10.21,Director,,0,0,0,,and then one shot per character,\Nwith them playing the game for real.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.71,1:07:13.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- I didn't touch!\N- I win.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.22,1:07:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I win.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.34,1:07:15.97,Director,,0,0,0,,These are tricky scenes,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.09,1:07:19.47,Director,,0,0,0,,especially for the director,\Nbecause they are joyful to shoot.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.64,1:07:21.89,Director,,0,0,0,,You feel as if you've got\Nlots of material
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.02,1:07:24.48,Director,,0,0,0,,and, as I found when filming with kids,\Na lot of charm,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.60,1:07:26.15,Director,,0,0,0,,but actually you need\Nto be clear-headed
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.27,1:07:27.86,Director,,0,0,0,,to make sure you get\Nthe material you need.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.98,1:07:31.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- You're cheating.\N- I'm not cheating, I play fast.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.73,1:07:33.61,Director,,0,0,0,,The first shot\Nis of Adèle Haenel
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.74,1:07:35.82,Director,,0,0,0,,and it reveals something of her,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.95,1:07:37.95,Director,,0,0,0,,something about her childhood.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.07,1:07:41.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Two. Two sixes.\N- Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.29,1:07:45.46,Director,,0,0,0,,We see her spontaneity\Nwhich flirts with the severing of ties
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.58,1:07:49.09,Director,,0,0,0,,but retains\Na rare form of innocence.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.25,1:07:50.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your turn.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.42,1:07:54.13,Director,,0,0,0,,The key shot in this sort of scene\Nis usually the last take,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.26,1:07:55.34,Director,,0,0,0,,which is of Noémie Merlant.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.47,1:07:57.64,Director,,0,0,0,,And I gave her a lot of directions
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.76,1:07:59.68,Director,,0,0,0,,because I saw\Nwhat the other actresses had given.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.81,1:08:06.81,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,CLAIRE MATHON: Céline wanted it\Nto be a film of faces.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.94,1:08:09.94,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,She wanted to film her actresses\Nand their faces.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.02,1:08:13.36,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,With the picture I tried not to show\Nthe direction or colour of the light.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.48,1:08:14.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncover your throat.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.65,1:08:17.49,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,I worked on getting\Na satin-smooth texture,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.61,1:08:19.70,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,on incorporating a softness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.03,1:08:24.08,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,Technically, that was created\Nthrough a mixture of filters
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.20,1:08:27.75,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,and the choice of the quality\Nand direction of the light,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.83,1:08:29.50,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,plus a collaboration with make-up.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.58,1:08:31.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have my future husband in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.17,1:08:35.51,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,What was beautiful was being able\Nto sense the slightest trembling,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.63,1:08:38.51,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,the slightest emotion,\Nwithout the light upstaging the actresses.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.59,1:08:42.72,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,Keeping the flesh tones,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.85,1:08:45.10,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,as if the light emanated\Nfrom their faces.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.22,1:08:46.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not men?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.85,1:08:50.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not allowed to.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.81,1:08:52.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.90,1:08:55.36,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,The film was shot\Nin a natural setting,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.48,1:09:00.16,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,but the light was mostly artificial.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.28,1:09:04.74,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,It was important to control the light\Nand choose how much to reveal.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.58,1:09:09.42,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,I also take inspiration\Nfrom accidental natural light effects,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.58,1:09:12.38,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,from the richness\Nof its reflections and flashes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.54,1:09:14.21,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,That's why I use\Na mixture of light sources
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.34,1:09:16.46,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,and work with successive layers
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.59,1:09:19.51,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,which the light shines through,\Ncreating reflections and diffusions.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.43,1:09:21.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's tolerated.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.55,1:09:24.93,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,Finding a balance between real life\Nand the timelessness of the portrait,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.06,1:09:29.06,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,being in the era whilst retaining\Nthe precision of a contemporary portrait.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.19,1:09:30.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...to amuse them?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.06,1:09:34.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Are you bored?\N- No.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.36,1:09:36.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.23,1:09:40.91,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,We were looking for clean lines,\Nespecially in the sets, the backgrounds.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.03,1:09:43.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your complexion is remarkable today.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.08,1:09:48.91,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,Céline's direction is very precise,\Nvery choreographed,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.00,1:09:52.88,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,which allowed for a picture
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.88,1:09:56.71,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,that was precise, subtle\Nand carefully chosen.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.84,1:09:58.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You pose beautifully.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.26,1:10:05.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're pretty.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.85,1:10:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I tell them.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.65,1:10:22.36,Director,,0,0,0,,SCIAMMA: This autumn bouquet.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.32,1:10:25.03,Director,,0,0,0,,A still life\Nthat is very much alive here
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.16,1:10:28.16,Director,,0,0,0,,but will be a bit less alive\Nlater on in the film.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.70,1:10:30.71,Director,,0,0,0,,And embroidery.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.79,1:10:33.92,Director,,0,0,0,,It was very important for me\Nthat embroidery should figure in the film,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.00,1:10:38.55,Director,,0,0,0,,a typically feminine art\Nwhich was then relegated to a craft
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.67,1:10:42.26,Director,,0,0,0,,to play down the importance\Nof the talent and contribution of women
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.38,1:10:44.97,Director,,0,0,0,,in the arts that they were allowed\Nto partake of.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.77,1:11:01.36,Director,,0,0,0,,And this shot which is an attempt\Nto embody the experience of sisterhood,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.49,1:11:02.70,Director,,0,0,0,,in other words,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.36,1:11:06.87,Director,,0,0,0,,a reversal of social roles
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.95,1:11:12.83,Director,,0,0,0,,and the sense of well-being\Nthat flows from that.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.13,1:11:28.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Then, striking the lyre\Nto accompany his words, he sang... "
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.89,1:11:32.77,Director,,0,0,0,,This sequence was\Na very late addition to the screenplay
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.89,1:11:34.69,Director,,0,0,0,,It was almost...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.81,1:11:40.11,Director,,0,0,0,,The dynamic of Orpheus and Eurydice\Nin the film was the last thing I wrote.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.23,1:11:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,poisoned her\Nand robbed her of her youth... "
Dialogue: 0,1:11:43.07,1:11:49.74,Director,,0,0,0,,I wanted a scene based on a story\Nto show the complicity between them,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.91,1:11:52.24,Director,,0,0,0,,a real Netflix-and-chill scene
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.37,1:11:56.33,Director,,0,0,0,,with a story with a very strong climax,\Ngenerating something to discuss,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.50,1:12:02.09,Director,,0,0,0,,because I wanted to see them\Nexchanging and putting forward theories
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.21,1:12:04.80,Director,,0,0,0,,about fiction\Nand the issues it raises.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.72,1:12:08.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"'If the fates refuse my wife this favour,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.55,1:12:11.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'I am determined not to return."
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.39,1:12:17.19,Director,,0,0,0,,This also introduces a feminist\Nreinterpretation of the myths.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.31,1:12:23.28,Director,,0,0,0,,The myth about Orpheus and Eurydice\Nhas been reinterpreted
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.40,1:12:26.20,Director,,0,0,0,,by numerous feminists,\Nnotably Monique Wittig,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.32,1:12:31.87,Director,,0,0,0,,because it is the myth which grants\Nthe male gaze the power to kill,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.99,1:12:35.50,Director,,0,0,0,,or to limit and condition.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.41,1:12:38.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"They sent for Eurydice.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.12,1:12:41.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was there,\Namong the recent spirits,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.42,1:12:42.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and approached, limping... "
Dialogue: 0,1:12:42.75,1:12:47.26,Director,,0,0,0,,This brings the myth up to date,\Nfirst in the act of reading and listening,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.18,1:12:50.18,Director,,0,0,0,,and then in the analysis.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.30,1:12:51.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"...or the favour would be void. "
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.80,1:12:54.43,Director,,0,0,0,,But there was an innocence\Nabout my including this myth.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.60,1:12:57.94,Director,,0,0,0,,I had no idea\Nhow far-reaching it would be in the story.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.06,1:13:03.32,Director,,0,0,0,,In the end it provided a link\Nbetween the two main threads
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.44,1:13:06.78,Director,,0,0,0,,which are the current experience of love\Nand the memory of that love.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.90,1:13:10.20,Director,,0,0,0,,The apparitions\Nof Héloïse as a ghost
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.32,1:13:12.53,Director,,0,0,0,,are the future imprint
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.58,1:13:16.12,Director,,0,0,0,,or the imprint already made
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.95,1:13:18.87,Director,,0,0,0,,by this myth\Nof Orpheus and Eurydice.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.96,1:13:21.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"She reached out for his embrace\Nand wished to hold him.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.08,1:13:25.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her poor hands\Nclutched only the empty air.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.05,1:13:27.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dying a second time,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.05,1:13:29.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she did not complain. "
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.38,1:13:31.59,Director,,0,0,0,,Dying twice is a woman's destiny.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.18,1:13:34.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's horrible.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.06,1:13:37.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Poor woman.\NWhy did he turn?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.14,1:13:39.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was told not to but did,\Nfor no reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.77,1:13:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are reasons.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.27,1:13:43.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think so? Read it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.65,1:13:46.11,Director,,0,0,0,,The joy of filming women\Nwho think and debate.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.61,1:13:52.32,Director,,0,0,0,,But also the joy of validity,\Nof the importance of all the theories.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.45,1:13:55.12,Director,,0,0,0,,No one is right and no one is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.24,1:13:58.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he can't look at her\Nfor fear of losing her.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.75,1:14:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's no reason.\NHe was told not to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.08,1:14:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's madly in love. He can't resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.38,1:14:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think Sophie has a point.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.55,1:14:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could resist.\NHis reasons aren't serious.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.47,1:14:12.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he makes a choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.34,1:14:13.93,Director,,0,0,0,,Marianne's theory is like her.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:14.05,1:14:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He chooses the memory of her.\NThat's why he turns.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.10,1:14:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He doesn't make the lover's choice,\Nbut the poet's.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.06,1:14:30.99,Director,,0,0,0,,The poet's choice,\Nand the debate is taken further.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.11,1:14:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"She spoke a last farewell
Dialogue: 0,1:14:33.91,1:14:36.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that scarcely reached his ears
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.66,1:14:38.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and fell back into the abyss. "
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.38,1:14:49.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps she was the one who said,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.46,1:14:51.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Turn around. "
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.72,1:14:54.14,Director,,0,0,0,,The myth\Nfrom Eurydice's point of view.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.26,1:14:56.18,Director,,0,0,0,,Love as admiration,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.14,1:15:00.85,Director,,0,0,0,,being impressed by someone.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.73,1:15:07.15,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,MATHON: It was important\Nto get a sense of the environment,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.27,1:15:09.61,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,to link the scene by the fireside\Nwith the moors.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.73,1:15:13.32,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,It's a more nocturnal sensation,\Nthe notion of silhouettes.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.11,1:15:18.08,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,This was obviously\Na key scene in the film,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.20,1:15:19.79,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,one of the formative scenes.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.25,1:15:24.17,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to be too realistic,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.29,1:15:26.71,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,too constrained by the flames.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.79,1:15:30.05,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,This whole sequence\Ntakes place around the fire,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.17,1:15:31.59,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,but you see very little of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.55,1:15:34.93,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,We set it up at the start.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.05,1:15:38.30,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,Then we retain this image for the shot\Nof the portrait of the lady on fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.06,1:15:47.65,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,I wanted the backgrounds\Nto convey a sense of the vegetation
Dialogue: 0,1:15:48.48,1:15:52.69,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,by giving depth to the image\Nwith its hazy light.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.53,1:16:02.24,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,That allowed me to be less monochrome\Nand to keep the colours subtle.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.37,1:16:04.12,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,It was very important to me\Nto keep the warmth
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.25,1:16:07.04,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,without losing the tones\Nof the skin and the costumes.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.34,1:16:16.34,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,The light came from a combination\Nof artificial sources and the fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.39,1:16:21.85,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,The fire was often replaced by gas lights\Nto temper the flames.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.97,1:16:25.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She says I'm still pregnant\Nand to come back in two days.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.35,1:16:27.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll come with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.36,1:16:34.57,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,The artificial lights allowed me to choose\Nthe direction of the light on the faces
Dialogue: 0,1:16:34.69,1:16:38.07,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,and to retain a softness,\Nbecause a flame is a harsh light.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.12,1:16:42.79,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,Also to limit the variation in the light,\Nthe flickering of the flames,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.29,1:16:46.54,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,which was too much,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.62,1:16:49.50,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,vying for attention\Nwith the facial expressions.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.67,1:16:56.55,Director,,0,0,0,,SCIAMMA: The first musical scene in the film,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:58.01,1:16:59.76,Director,,0,0,0,,a piece composed for the film,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.89,1:17:01.97,Director,,0,0,0,,its anthem or perhaps\Nan anthem for something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.72,1:17:07.10,Director,,0,0,0,,I asked for something\Npolyphonic, polyrhythmic,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.23,1:17:09.73,Director,,0,0,0,,with a high number of beats per minute\Nto evoke a trance.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.77,1:17:13.65,Director,,0,0,0,,The scene starts\Nwith a sort of normality,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.77,1:17:16.99,Director,,0,0,0,,the idea of women\Nmeeting round a fire
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.11,1:17:19.36,Director,,0,0,0,,to drink and chat.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.49,1:17:22.58,Director,,0,0,0,,This was about friendship. Maybe\Nfriends is what so-called witches were.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.53,1:17:26.25,Director,,0,0,0,,And then their song,\Nwhich fires up the imagination.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.12,1:17:28.62,Director,,0,0,0,,We had the tools of filmmaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.17,1:17:33.09,Director,,0,0,0,,We started\Nwith a really realistic sound.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.17,1:17:37.63,Director,,0,0,0,,These women were singing on set.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.67,1:17:43.60,Director,,0,0,0,,But we soon mixed in bigger sounds\Nthan the sounds on set.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.93,1:17:46.47,Director,,0,0,0,,And we weren't afraid to go for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.98,1:17:56.78,Director,,0,0,0,,This group scene\Nis also a love scene.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.86,1:17:59.15,Director,,0,0,0,,These women singing
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.28,1:18:03.20,Director,,0,0,0,,accompanies\Nthe first exchange of smiles
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.28,1:18:07.04,Director,,0,0,0,,between the two main characters\None hour and ten minutes into the film.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.42,1:18:15.88,Director,,0,0,0,,The words are in Latin.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.00,1:18:19.51,Director,,0,0,0,,It's a rough translation of a line\Nby Nietzsche which says:
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.63,1:18:23.22,Director,,0,0,0,,{\i0}"The higher we soar, the smaller\Nwe appear to those who cannot fly."{\i1}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.64,1:18:31.85,Director,,0,0,0,,The desired image,\Nthe eponymous image.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.65,1:18:35.94,Director,,0,0,0,,Literally setting the character on fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.78,1:18:39.15,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,MATHON: I remember the moment I realised
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.99,1:18:42.41,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,the extent to which a painting\Nis not a photograph of an instant
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.53,1:18:45.57,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,but a much freer interpretation
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.70,1:18:47.28,Cinematographer,,0,0,0,,despite its realism.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.37,1:18:52.04,Director,,0,0,0,,SCIAMMA: The link shot of the extended hand
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.96,1:18:55.92,Director,,0,0,0,,towards another space-time
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.04,1:18:57.55,Director,,0,0,0,,was written into the screenplay.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.34,1:19:00.84,Director,,0,0,0,,It's a leap.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.97,1:19:03.80,Director,,0,0,0,,Overall in the film\Nwe did a lot of work on scenes
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.93,1:19:06.76,Director,,0,0,0,,which started as one thing\Nand became something else.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.89,1:19:10.81,Director,,0,0,0,,And for this scene of the first kiss\Nthe opposite was true.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.93,1:19:13.94,Director,,0,0,0,,We go from one scene to the next\Nwith a radical ellipsis.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.44,1:19:19.90,Director,,0,0,0,,This scene of the first kiss,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.82,1:19:25.36,Director,,0,0,0,,a lot of thought went into it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.24,1:19:29.04,Director,,0,0,0,,How do you film a first kiss?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.16,1:19:31.33,Director,,0,0,0,,What is a first kiss?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.79,1:19:36.58,Director,,0,0,0,,What will we remember
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.00,1:19:39.92,Director,,0,0,0,,about what leads to the kiss?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.05,1:19:42.38,Director,,0,0,0,,And it's that choreography\Nwe are thinking of.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.67,1:19:48.55,Director,,0,0,0,,The long tracking shot of the rocks\Nand then this link shot of her walking.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.68,1:19:52.39,Director,,0,0,0,,And these scarves\Nwhich were intended for this scene.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.52,1:19:55.44,Director,,0,0,0,,Because we wanted\Nto show their faces afresh
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.56,1:19:58.36,Director,,0,0,0,,and to work\Non the eroticism of consent
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.98,1:20:02.23,Director,,0,0,0,,with the idea\Nthat they would uncover their mouths
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.11,1:20:11.66,Director,,0,0,0,,and the fabric dancing on their lips\Nwould show their heavy breathing.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:16.29,1:20:17.79,Director,,0,0,0,,The cave, the sound work.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.79,1:20:22.84,Director,,0,0,0,,Their hearts beating,\Nthe tide coming in.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:25.17,1:20:27.22,Director,,0,0,0,,Their hearts in their stomachs.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.89,1:20:39.73,Director,,0,0,0,,From that moment on,\Nthe pace of the film changes.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.86,1:20:43.73,Director,,0,0,0,,Another new chapter:\NThe inevitable happens.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.57,1:20:48.41,Director,,0,0,0,,From now on time passes differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.42,1:21:03.88,Director,,0,0,0,,With the help of sequence shots\Nwe create new pulsations.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.42,1:21:09.22,Director,,0,0,0,,The same grammar,\Ndifferent rules.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.42,1:21:41.17,Director,,0,0,0,,It's coq au vin.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.21,1:21:47.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about Héloïse?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.21,1:21:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She isn't well.\NShe doesn't want dinner.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:58.81,1:22:01.52,Director,,0,0,0,,Here the fantasy dimension\Nreasserts itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.65,1:22:04.27,Director,,0,0,0,,and you sense that from the sound.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.86,1:22:07.65,Director,,0,0,0,,The sound is spatialised.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:15.99,1:22:18.58,Director,,0,0,0,,It also conveys\Nreverberations, the breath.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.92,1:22:29.80,Director,,0,0,0,,This apparition of Héloïse\Nwas a camera effect.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.80,1:22:35.55,Director,,0,0,0,,The beauty of camera effects\Nin filmmaking
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.68,1:22:38.14,Director,,0,0,0,,is that they are tried and tested,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.27,1:22:40.56,Director,,0,0,0,,but you always feel\Nas if you are inventing something new,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.69,1:22:43.60,Director,,0,0,0,,because you have to invent something,\Nto construct something,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.73,1:22:45.69,Director,,0,0,0,,to create this image of the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.74,1:22:51.78,Director,,0,0,0,,It requires a lot of faith.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.90,1:22:53.24,Director,,0,0,0,,It's very religious.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.08,1:22:57.41,Director,,0,0,0,,And here...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:59.37,1:23:02.25,Director,,0,0,0,,...the only shot to quote another film.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.00,1:23:13.34,Director,,0,0,0,,This shot, which is a nod\Nto {\i0}Persona{\i1} by Bergman,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.47,1:23:17.10,Director,,0,0,0,,especially through the next link shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.40,1:23:32.36,Director,,0,0,0,,It's a quotation\Nand yet you always think...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.90,1:23:36.37,Director,,0,0,0,,...when you love someone\Nthat you're inventing something new.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.91,1:23:45.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought you had been scared off.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.71,1:23:49.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were right.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.38,1:23:51.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.48,1:24:13.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do all lovers feel\Nthey're inventing something?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.87,1:24:20.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know the gestures.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.75,1:24:24.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I imagined it all, waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.83,1:24:27.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You dreamt of me?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.30,1:24:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.41,1:25:05.66,Director,,0,0,0,,Sophie.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.79,1:25:11.79,Director,,0,0,0,,A bit more of an expectation\Nthat she will behave as a servant.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.92,1:25:14.59,Director,,0,0,0,,She knocks on the door.\NWhat goes on behind closed doors?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.67,1:25:16.59,Director,,0,0,0,,But that's not the issue for her.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.72,1:25:18.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.26,1:25:20.89,Director,,0,0,0,,The issue is whether or not\Nthey're going to accompany her.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.14,1:25:24.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get up.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.22,1:25:27.02,Director,,0,0,0,,The intimacy of the morning after\Nrather than the night before.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.86,1:25:32.65,Director,,0,0,0,,Marianne has her hands\Nin her pockets.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.77,1:25:34.69,Director,,0,0,0,,It's an important detail.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.86,1:25:39.20,Director,,0,0,0,,I was obsessed,\Nwhen we were creating the costumes,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.32,1:25:41.24,Director,,0,0,0,,with the character having pockets.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.37,1:25:43.33,Director,,0,0,0,,Noémie Merlant had\Na whole file on pockets.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.45,1:25:45.95,Director,,0,0,0,,She knew when she was meant\Nto put her hands in her pockets.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.21,1:25:51.38,Director,,0,0,0,,The shape seems modern,\Nbut it's not anachronistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.54,1:25:52.96,Director,,0,0,0,,Women had pockets\Nin those days.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.09,1:25:55.55,Director,,0,0,0,,They removed them in the 19th century,\Nlike so many other things.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.01,1:26:03.10,Director,,0,0,0,,The scene of the abortion\Nwas very tricky to film.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.22,1:26:05.47,Director,,0,0,0,,We shot it at the end\Nof the first week.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.60,1:26:09.27,Director,,0,0,0,,We only visited the location once.\NIt was a sort of museum.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.10,1:26:13.19,Director,,0,0,0,,Those sorts of sets aren't ideal.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.73,1:26:18.24,Director,,0,0,0,,There are extras, characters\Nwho only appear once.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.36,1:26:20.65,Director,,0,0,0,,That's Christel Baras,\Nthe casting director.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.32,1:26:24.74,Director,,0,0,0,,She's a great actress.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.74,1:26:29.46,Director,,0,0,0,,And the biggest challenge\Nin this scene
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.16,1:26:31.58,Director,,0,0,0,,was the child.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.63,1:26:33.71,Director,,0,0,0,,A young child.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.34,1:26:39.67,Director,,0,0,0,,And the scene revolves\Naround the child.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:41.76,1:26:42.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lie down.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.89,1:26:45.35,Director,,0,0,0,,When you get ready to shoot\Na scene like this,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.47,1:26:48.85,Director,,0,0,0,,you feel very alone,\Nbecause there are no pointers,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.97,1:26:50.52,Director,,0,0,0,,there are very few instances of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.64,1:26:52.90,Director,,0,0,0,,There are no precedents\Nin the history of filmmaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.52,1:26:58.73,Director,,0,0,0,,And I took little pleasure\Nin being a pioneer.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.86,1:27:02.15,Director,,0,0,0,,Calling people pioneers\Nis just a way of rewarding those
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.24,1:27:05.70,Director,,0,0,0,,who feel as if they're doing\Nsomething for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.83,1:27:06.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Deep breaths.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.95,1:27:08.16,Director,,0,0,0,,But it's not enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.58,1:27:11.29,Director,,0,0,0,,It's not enough to be landed\Nwith the scene.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.41,1:27:14.04,Director,,0,0,0,,You need to love it,\Nthere needs to be a desire for it,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.21,1:27:17.25,Director,,0,0,0,,something unique to the film,\Nand what's unique here is the child.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.59,1:27:23.26,Director,,0,0,0,,Filming with a child requires
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.93,1:27:26.01,Director,,0,0,0,,maximum comfort for the child
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.14,1:27:28.14,Director,,0,0,0,,which means minimum comfort for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.18,1:27:33.69,Director,,0,0,0,,And you have to...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.10,1:27:38.40,Director,,0,0,0,,...have faith in a very long take.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.52,1:27:42.53,Director,,0,0,0,,You link the shots.\NI was sitting just beside them.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.65,1:27:46.03,Director,,0,0,0,,I was right beside Luàna Bajrami,\Nthe actress.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.62,1:27:48.03,Director,,0,0,0,,I talked her through it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:49.54,1:27:53.66,Director,,0,0,0,,And it was a question\Nof when to start and when to finish,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.79,1:27:56.71,Director,,0,0,0,,making sure the child was OK\Nand trusting her.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.42,1:28:00.67,Director,,0,0,0,,The child was meant\Nto put his hand on her chest.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.80,1:28:03.05,Director,,0,0,0,,That was in the screenplay.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.30,1:28:05.76,Director,,0,0,0,,Instead he wiped away her tears.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.81,1:28:12.93,Director,,0,0,0,,Those weren't miracles,\Nthey were decisions.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:14.94,1:28:16.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:18.19,1:28:19.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll watch over her.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.82,1:28:23.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to go to bed.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.36,1:28:26.99,Director,,0,0,0,,This was a link shot\Nthat I knew to be disturbing.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.11,1:28:28.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sophie?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.45,1:28:30.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you asleep?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.25,1:28:38.83,Director,,0,0,0,,Because, straight after that scene\Ndepicting the abortion,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.29,1:28:47.05,Director,,0,0,0,,we enter a new dynamic\Nand the abortion is re-enacted.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.22,1:28:50.55,Director,,0,0,0,,It was very important to me,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.68,1:28:55.85,Director,,0,0,0,,even if it has a double-trigger effect,\Nor rather a double-tension one.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.48,1:29:00.86,Director,,0,0,0,,It was important\Nto show both the abortion
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.98,1:29:04.32,Director,,0,0,0,,and the importance\Nof showing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.44,1:29:06.40,Director,,0,0,0,,Because that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.53,1:29:09.03,Director,,0,0,0,,That's what happened
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.16,1:29:11.70,Director,,0,0,0,,when women were denied\Nthe opportunity to be artists.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.79,1:29:16.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get your things.\NWe're going to paint.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.66,1:29:19.38,Director,,0,0,0,,They didn't paint their private lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.79,1:29:24.42,Director,,0,0,0,,They didn't paint their desires,\Nthey didn't paint their bodies.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.59,1:29:26.05,Director,,0,0,0,,They didn't paint their lives
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.97,1:29:31.35,Director,,0,0,0,,And all these images are missing\Nfrom art history but also from our lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.14,1:29:35.06,Director,,0,0,0,,It was Annie Ernaux who said\Nthat in no museum in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.18,1:29:37.81,Director,,0,0,0,,is there a painting called\N{\i0}"The Backstreet Abortionist"{\i1}.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:41.81,1:29:45.15,Director,,0,0,0,,So this scene comes\Na bit too quickly, perhaps, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.57,1:29:49.11,Director,,0,0,0,,...it's so we don't forget.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.24,1:29:50.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at her.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.36,1:29:52.74,Director,,0,0,0,,It's so we don't forget\Nthat art creates memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.91,1:29:54.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Arch your back a little.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.79,1:30:00.83,Director,,0,0,0,,And I also wanted\Nto show the pleasure...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.92,1:30:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Straighten your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.21,1:30:04.09,Director,,0,0,0,,...of showing,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.17,1:30:07.26,Director,,0,0,0,,which we see on Marianne's face.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.38,1:30:11.80,Director,,0,0,0,,And also to show\Nthe model's impulse,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.93,1:30:13.26,Director,,0,0,0,,her intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.43,1:30:15.93,Director,,0,0,0,,She tells us what to look at.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.06,1:30:18.56,Director,,0,0,0,,She had the idea of painting it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.68,1:30:22.44,Director,,0,0,0,,Women's only chance\Nto be in artists' studios
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.56,1:30:25.78,Director,,0,0,0,,was as models,\Nand they seized that opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.90,1:30:27.53,Director,,0,0,0,,That's how they created\Nworks of art.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.37,1:30:36.62,Director,,0,0,0,,This is my favourite painting.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.50,1:30:40.92,Director,,0,0,0,,It was never finished.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.44,1:31:04.36,Director,,0,0,0,,Another painting about desire.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.48,1:31:07.07,Director,,0,0,0,,Sending out signals.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.19,1:31:11.07,Director,,0,0,0,,Conveying desire in the film\Nrested on their shoulders.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.70,1:31:14.16,Director,,0,0,0,,Sending signals and receiving them.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.28,1:31:15.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.70,1:31:23.25,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,MERLANT: Adèle and I didn't work\Non our relationship before filming.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:23.29,1:31:24.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be serious.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.46,1:31:26.75,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,We didn't prepare the scenes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.92,1:31:28.38,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,On the contrary, it was created
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.42,1:31:33.72,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,in an environment\Nof collaboration and benevolence.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.84,1:31:35.85,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,From the start, a horizontal look,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.97,1:31:38.64,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,and it's that horizontal look\Nthat the film is about,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.76,1:31:40.89,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,the way collaborators\Nlook at one another.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.02,1:31:45.27,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,That vision that Céline shares\Nin her way of working
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.40,1:31:48.69,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,helped us to form this relationship.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.23,1:31:52.19,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,Adèle and I formed a relationship,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.32,1:31:54.86,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,getting to know one another\Nas the shoot went on.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.99,1:31:56.57,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,We observed one another.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:56.70,1:32:01.37,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,We used that to create the relationship\Nbetween Héloïse and Marianne.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.55,1:32:14.09,Director,,0,0,0,,SCIAMMA: A show of intimacy, of nudity.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.38,1:32:16.55,Director,,0,0,0,,And sexuality.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.89,1:32:21.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bought it from a woman at the feast.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.85,1:32:27.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a plant.\NShe said it makes you fly.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.23,1:32:32.11,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,HAENEL: Generally in films,\Nshooting sex scenes is stressful
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.23,1:32:34.11,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,because there's no idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.45,1:32:40.91,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,So, as an actor, you find yourself\Nhaving to simulate coitus in a wide shot
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.04,1:32:45.21,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,and you feel extremely vulnerable\Nbecause your body is on display,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.33,1:32:46.54,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,which is very intimate,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.08,1:32:49.50,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,and you're not given any direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.67,1:32:53.80,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,What's great about this film\Nis that there is eroticism,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.97,1:32:58.97,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,but it is sheltered by an idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.81,1:33:07.85,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,For me the idea of penetrating\Nthe armpits added a sort of humour
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.98,1:33:09.61,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,which is often lacking in sex scenes.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.73,1:33:13.44,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,Generally sex scenes reflect\Nthe way they are done,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.57,1:33:16.03,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,they reflect a moment on set.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.66,1:33:21.20,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,This moment on set was joyful.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.79,1:33:27.62,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,And I was very happy\Nto be able to take part
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.75,1:33:30.58,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,in a sort of demonstration
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.75,1:33:32.92,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,that eroticism is linked\Nto the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.97,1:33:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.03,1:33:56.99,Director,,0,0,0,,SCIAMMA: The second scene\Nwith the ghostly apparition.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.78,1:34:01.57,Director,,0,0,0,,A good rule for a screenplay\Nis a rule of three.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.70,1:34:06.83,Director,,0,0,0,,And it plants the idea\Nthat Marianne is tempted by an image
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.95,1:34:09.42,Director,,0,0,0,,which seems to be in the future.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.54,1:34:14.21,Director,,0,0,0,,To my mind love affairs\Nare always haunted by their ending.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.81,1:34:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have to drink.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.03,1:34:45.79,Director,,0,0,0,,This was an attempt\Nto democratise this motif.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.37,1:35:28.99,Director,,0,0,0,,This was one of the scenes\Nwe did the most takes for.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:32.79,1:35:38.05,Director,,0,0,0,,It's the film's main scene for dialogue\Nand possibly for conflict too.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.17,1:35:40.88,Director,,0,0,0,,But it's not orchestrated\Nas a scene of conflict.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.01,1:35:44.47,Director,,0,0,0,,It's not orchestrated\Nas arguments and negotiations.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.39,1:35:51.73,Director,,0,0,0,,The power struggle between the two\Nis a discourse.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.56,1:35:58.40,Director,,0,0,0,,And that's the real pleasure,\Nthe challenge of the film,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.48,1:36:00.86,Director,,0,0,0,,to show characters\Nwho are in a dialogue with one another.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.07,1:36:06.37,Director,,0,0,0,,They listen to one another\Nand bounce ideas off one another.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.62,1:36:10.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't destroy the last one for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.70,1:36:13.50,Director,,0,0,0,,There was a basic desire to create\Na sense of the present tense...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.58,1:36:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did it for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.79,1:36:16.75,Director,,0,0,0,,...through something written,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.92,1:36:19.71,Director,,0,0,0,,and people know it's written
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.88,1:36:22.72,Director,,0,0,0,,because the dialogue is literary.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.84,1:36:24.93,Director,,0,0,0,,But there's a pleasure\Nin creating a present
Dialogue: 0,1:36:25.05,1:36:27.39,Director,,0,0,0,,because the characters' thinking\Nis in the present
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.51,1:36:31.18,Director,,0,0,0,,and enacted by the actresses\Nin the present.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:33.35,1:36:34.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Through it, I give you to another.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.77,1:36:36.40,Director,,0,0,0,,It was one of the pleasures...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.44,1:36:41.98,Director,,0,0,0,,...of these scenes with dialogue
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.11,1:36:44.53,Director,,0,0,0,,which have the vocation\Nof conveying the spoken word.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.66,1:36:54.50,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,HAENEL: This scene didn't necessarily go\Nto where we imagined it would.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:54.62,1:36:56.50,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,Now you possess me a little,\Nyou bear me a grudge.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.58,1:36:59.96,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,MERLANT: Yes, I expressed a lot of anger\Nin the first takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.04,1:37:02.92,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,Then it was your turn.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.09,1:37:07.68,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,HAENEL: I was more expressive to start with,\Nthen the idea was to rein in the emotion
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.80,1:37:13.68,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,and to make it less explosive\Nand more horizontal.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.81,1:37:15.31,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,I did my takes
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.43,1:37:17.73,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,and we ended up\Nwith what's in the film,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:17.85,1:37:19.81,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,something much more controlled,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.94,1:37:23.19,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,and as a result\Nyou asked to do another take.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.11,1:37:26.99,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,MERLANT: I asked to redo a take...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.16,1:37:32.08,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,...where everything\Nwas more reined in and contained.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.20,1:37:34.20,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,- HAENEL: And still.\N{\c&H0000FF&}- MERLANT: Yes, still,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:34.33,1:37:36.79,'Marianne',,0,0,0,,compared to the first take\Nwhich was much more...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.91,1:37:39.00,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,- HAENEL: ...agitated.\N{\c&H0000FF&}- MERLANT: Agitated, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.55,1:37:43.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it then.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:45.13,1:37:46.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You find me docile.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.51,1:37:48.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Worse...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.18,1:37:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You imagine I'm collusive.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.14,1:37:55.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You imagine my pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.31,1:37:57.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a way of avoiding hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.89,1:38:01.81,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,HAENEL: There was the sense that\Nif we overdid it, the information got lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.94,1:38:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...happy or unhappy...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.77,1:38:08.49,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,The idea for us as actors\Nis to unfold the emotions,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.61,1:38:10.99,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,to give them a rhythm.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.12,1:38:13.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd prefer me to resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:15.04,1:38:16.58,Director,,0,0,0,,SCIAMMA: Here you've got ambiguity.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:17.96,1:38:19.21,Director,,0,0,0,,Yes, she'd prefer her to resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.37,1:38:20.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you asking me to?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.92,1:38:25.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Answer me.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.55,1:38:31.51,Director,,0,0,0,,"No, I'm not asking you to"\Nor, "No, I'm not answering"?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.02,1:38:44.02,Director,,0,0,0,,The still life\Nwith a bit less life in it now.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.07,1:38:54.49,Director,,0,0,0,,A vanitas.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.95,1:38:59.58,Director,,0,0,0,,The rapid footsteps
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.71,1:39:01.62,Director,,0,0,0,,which, as so often in the film,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.75,1:39:02.96,Director,,0,0,0,,herald an announcement.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.00,1:39:04.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you seen Héloïse?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.00,1:39:07.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. She isn't in her room.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.97,1:39:12.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've had news.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.68,1:39:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Madam returns tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.01,1:39:18.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.89,1:39:20.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you be ready?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:22.73,1:39:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.24,1:39:35.12,Director,,0,0,0,,It's been a while\Nsince we were outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:37.16,1:39:40.20,Director,,0,0,0,,This scene was filmed\Non the third day of shooting.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.33,1:39:44.29,Director,,0,0,0,,It was the first big scene\Nof intimacy that we shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.46,1:39:46.67,Director,,0,0,0,,We spent a lot of time\Ngetting the level of emotion right.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.13,1:39:51.55,Director,,0,0,0,,This was one of the last takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.67,1:39:55.34,Director,,0,0,0,,For ages when we were editing the film\NI found the first take to be
Dialogue: 0,1:39:56.35,1:39:58.81,Director,,0,0,0,,good, satisfactory, moving.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.93,1:40:03.69,Director,,0,0,0,,It was a take\Nwhere the emotion was less buried.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:05.31,1:40:09.86,Director,,0,0,0,,And in the end we chose this one
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.94,1:40:12.65,Director,,0,0,0,,which was more bathed in tears
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.70,1:40:15.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your mother returns tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.41,1:40:18.08,Director,,0,0,0,,More devastating,\Nfor Marianne in particular.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.95,1:40:24.17,Director,,0,0,0,,She's the character\Nwho lays bare her emotions
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.29,1:40:25.50,Director,,0,0,0,,in the film.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.29,1:40:30.00,Director,,0,0,0,,This was the eighth take.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.17,1:40:35.47,Director,,0,0,0,,There is exhaustion, tension, abandon.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.68,1:40:39.35,Director,,0,0,0,,And Noémie Merlant's tears.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.19,1:40:45.81,Director,,0,0,0,,We kept it long.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.70,1:41:06.62,Director,,0,0,0,,Now, after that last outpouring
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.79,1:41:08.75,Director,,0,0,0,,with the waves, the ocean,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.83,1:41:12.09,Director,,0,0,0,,the sound is really spare.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.21,1:41:15.55,Director,,0,0,0,,There's no such thing as silence\Nin the cinema. Something always fills it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.26,1:41:22.77,Director,,0,0,0,,Obviously, the sound here is spatialised\Nso there is more than one thing filling it,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:22.89,1:41:25.98,Director,,0,0,0,,maybe five things at any one time.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.10,1:41:28.44,Director,,0,0,0,,It takes a lot of reflection\Nto create silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:28.56,1:41:31.65,Director,,0,0,0,,What is the silence made of?\NWhat note? What wind?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.28,1:41:36.07,Director,,0,0,0,,Do you want it to be felt?\NDo you want it to be ignored?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.70,1:41:40.99,Director,,0,0,0,,Here we are just left\Nwith the voices
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.12,1:41:43.49,Director,,0,0,0,,and the bodies.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.62,1:41:47.87,Director,,0,0,0,,Silence is also about making room\Nfor the bodies,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.00,1:41:51.67,Director,,0,0,0,,for the sound of the bodies\Nof the characters and the actors,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.79,1:41:54.51,Director,,0,0,0,,the direct sound of their breath.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.59,1:41:58.76,Director,,0,0,0,,And this silence relies\Non being able to listen.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.88,1:42:02.26,Director,,0,0,0,,We always think of the sensations,\Nof the sensory experience
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.39,1:42:05.18,Director,,0,0,0,,the film gives the audience.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.31,1:42:08.89,Director,,0,0,0,,This silence makes them\Nlisten to their own breath.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.02,1:42:13.77,Director,,0,0,0,,They are sharing the space\Nwith their neighbours' bodies
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.90,1:42:16.57,Director,,0,0,0,,and the emotions can be heard.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.45,1:42:28.21,Director,,0,0,0,,And the listening experience\Nyou create with a void
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.37,1:42:32.79,Director,,0,0,0,,makes the audience focus\Nand pay attention
Dialogue: 0,1:42:32.92,1:42:35.55,Director,,0,0,0,,to their own emotion.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:45.81,1:42:46.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finished.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.40,1:42:54.27,Director,,0,0,0,,The portrait is done,\Nbut the story carries on.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.94,1:42:58.24,Director,,0,0,0,,With another portrait.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.36,1:42:59.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is that for?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.86,1:43:02.45,Director,,0,0,0,,Here the idea was\Nto show the miniatures.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:02.57,1:43:06.87,Director,,0,0,0,,Miniatures were often painted\Nby women
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.99,1:43:10.50,Director,,0,0,0,,and that's partly why\Nso many of them are lost.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.66,1:43:14.84,Director,,0,0,0,,Miniatures are lost\Nin private collections.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:16.63,1:43:20.42,Director,,0,0,0,,These great little works\Nare not in our archives.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.55,1:43:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After a while,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.34,1:43:27.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you'll see her\Nwhen you think of me.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:27.18,1:43:30.31,Director,,0,0,0,,There is something very contemporary\Nabout this scene.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.43,1:43:32.52,Director,,0,0,0,,They have their hair down.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:32.65,1:43:33.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll have no image of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.98,1:43:38.61,Director,,0,0,0,,There are no costumes,\Njust the shoulders of naked bodies.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.73,1:43:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you want an image of me?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.07,1:43:43.16,Director,,0,0,0,,And we no longer know\Nwhich era this is.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:45.49,1:43:48.70,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,HAENEL: The point where I say 28...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:48.83,1:43:50.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That one.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:50.29,1:43:52.67,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,There was going to be\Na justification for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:52.79,1:43:54.50,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,Why 28?\NBecause it's my age.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:54.63,1:43:58.30,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,But we cut it,\Nand taking that decision on set meant
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.42,1:44:03.51,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,a new mystery was created because,\Nwithout the explanation, when I said...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.63,1:44:04.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Twenty-eight.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.89,1:44:08.93,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,When I said 28, I thought,\NI'm going to create a treasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:09.06,1:44:14.15,'Héloïse',,0,0,0,,No one else will know what it means,\Nbut it's meaningful to her at that moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.28,1:44:21.74,Director,,0,0,0,,SCIAMMA: The story really lends itself\Nto these scenes.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.86,1:44:26.45,Director,,0,0,0,,They are so charged\Nthat they become almost dreamlike.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.53,1:44:29.99,Director,,0,0,0,,One or two takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.20,1:44:35.54,Director,,0,0,0,,There's the idea of the mirror\Nin which the painter's face is reflected.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.71,1:44:37.96,Director,,0,0,0,,That was also a nod to...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.34,1:44:41.59,Director,,0,0,0,,...Francesca Woodman,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.30,1:44:44.76,Director,,0,0,0,,the photographer from New York.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.51,1:44:55.77,Director,,0,0,0,,This scene wasn't in the screenplay.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.90,1:45:01.40,Director,,0,0,0,,I wrote it specifically\Nfor the last round of auditions
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.53,1:45:03.78,Director,,0,0,0,,when we chose Noémie Merlant.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.99,1:45:10.41,Director,,0,0,0,,I had decided to write a scene\Nspecifically for the auditions,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.54,1:45:17.58,Director,,0,0,0,,a scene that would allow me\Nto evaluate the degree of intimacy,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.71,1:45:22.59,Director,,0,0,0,,the melodrama, the emotion,\Na scene with everything in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.67,1:45:27.05,Director,,0,0,0,,A farewell scene\Nbefore the farewells.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:28.05,1:45:30.68,Director,,0,0,0,,This scene was a determining factor,\Npractically a revelation,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.72,1:45:33.77,Director,,0,0,0,,in the choice of Noémie Merlant.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.44,1:45:41.23,Director,,0,0,0,,I filmed this scene\NI had written an hour previously.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.40,1:45:42.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:42.86,1:45:46.20,Director,,0,0,0,,It was moving and the scene worked.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.32,1:45:50.07,Director,,0,0,0,,In particular it worked between them,\Nthere was a real chemistry,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:50.20,1:45:53.20,Director,,0,0,0,,a real closeness,\Na real friendship...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.37,1:45:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll remember when you fell asleep\Nin the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.50,1:45:58.42,Director,,0,0,0,,It was very seductive\Nwithout any seducing.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.63,1:46:01.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll remember...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.30,1:46:04.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,your dark stare when I beat you at cards.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.88,1:46:07.22,Director,,0,0,0,,The electricity between them\Nwas so strong
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.34,1:46:11.47,Director,,0,0,0,,that, as I filmed the scene,\Nmy heart was pounding
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.60,1:46:12.97,Director,,0,0,0,,and I thought, "That's it."
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.97,1:46:17.85,Director,,0,0,0,,I saw a real equality.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.94,1:46:20.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You took your time being funny.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.73,1:46:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.73,1:46:24.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasted time.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:25.07,1:46:26.69,Director,,0,0,0,,Between the two lovers.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.82,1:46:28.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasted time, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:28.65,1:46:30.53,Director,,0,0,0,,It was something new
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.70,1:46:34.62,Director,,0,0,0,,and it was something\Nwe had created together.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.74,1:46:38.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,l'll remember the first time\NI wanted to kiss you.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:41.71,1:46:42.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When was that?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.79,1:46:48.17,Director,,0,0,0,,It's a top shot\Nso we had all the machinery in place
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.30,1:46:50.47,Director,,0,0,0,,in the background.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.59,1:46:52.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the gathering around the bonfire.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:52.47,1:46:54.64,Director,,0,0,0,,To show the point of view\Nof God, almost...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.72,1:46:55.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:55.85,1:46:57.10,Director,,0,0,0,,...of this intimate exchange.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.22,1:46:59.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that wasn't the first time.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.48,1:47:02.23,Director,,0,0,0,,My heart was beating so fast\Nduring these takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.36,1:47:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:05.11,1:47:06.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, you tell me.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:06.82,1:47:10.78,Director,,0,0,0,,We only shot four takes\Nfor this scene.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:13.32,1:47:15.95,Director,,0,0,0,,We worked on the lighting...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.08,1:47:17.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you asked\Nif had known love.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:17.70,1:47:22.63,Director,,0,0,0,,...on the way their hair is lit.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.71,1:47:24.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could tell the answer was yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:25.88,1:47:27.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that it was now.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.76,1:47:29.51,Director,,0,0,0,,It looks timeless.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.30,1:47:34.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.98,1:47:46.48,Director,,0,0,0,,I gave a lot of thought to this shot.\NIt may not look like much.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:46.65,1:47:50.70,Director,,0,0,0,,With scenes like that, you arrive on set\Nand no one knows how it will turn out.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.82,1:47:52.15,Director,,0,0,0,,You just know\Nyou have to shoot it.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:53.78,1:47:56.49,Director,,0,0,0,,And you spend time together,\Narranging the hair.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.96,1:48:08.25,Director,,0,0,0,,This sequence shot\Nhas a very particular rhythm.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.51,1:48:12.63,Director,,0,0,0,,A man enters the frame.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.76,1:48:13.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.05,1:48:15.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:17.89,1:48:20.81,Director,,0,0,0,,A good morning is enough\Nto remind us
Dialogue: 0,1:48:22.02,1:48:24.15,Director,,0,0,0,,of all the people\Nwhose story we haven't told.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:25.02,1:48:26.52,Director,,0,0,0,,It just takes a man's body...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:27.98,1:48:29.73,Director,,0,0,0,,...to tell the story we haven't told.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:30.94,1:48:32.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're here.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.86,1:48:35.95,Director,,0,0,0,,The film chose to tell the story\Nof a possible love affair.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:37.28,1:48:42.29,Director,,0,0,0,,In other words,\Nwhat it put in the centre of the frame
Dialogue: 0,1:48:42.41,1:48:44.58,Director,,0,0,0,,was what was possible,\Nwhat was bearable.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:44.75,1:48:47.17,Director,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's what it means\Nto create female characters,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:47.25,1:48:48.50,Director,,0,0,0,,to focus on their desires.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:48.67,1:48:52.76,Director,,0,0,0,,If you focus on their opportunities\Nthere isn't much to say.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:52.88,1:48:57.47,Director,,0,0,0,,And as soon as a film focuses\Non the desires of the characters...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:00.10,1:49:02.77,Director,,0,0,0,,Perhaps what makes it revolutionary\Nis giving them all the space.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:04.64,1:49:08.44,Director,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, all it takes\Nis a body in a frame to say...
Dialogue: 0,1:49:09.02,1:49:10.02,Director,,0,0,0,,danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:10.15,1:49:15.24,Director,,0,0,0,,Perhaps like a femme fatale in a film noir\Nwith a cigarette holder signalling danger.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.36,1:49:16.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very good.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:24.00,1:49:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For you.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.12,1:49:29.96,Director,,0,0,0,,There is an inevitability\Nabout what happens next.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.04,1:49:33.34,Director,,0,0,0,,The sound has been stripped\Nright back.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:37.18,1:49:40.81,Director,,0,0,0,,We return to the impediments.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.93,1:49:41.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In a minute.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:42.52,1:49:43.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, now.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.89,1:49:49.40,Director,,0,0,0,,But since we avoided the dynamic\Nof conflict and obstacles for so long,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.65,1:49:55.24,Director,,0,0,0,,it doesn't feel fictitious.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.36,1:49:58.78,Director,,0,0,0,,It is at once tragic,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:00.70,1:50:03.54,Director,,0,0,0,,political and intimate.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:24.85,1:50:29.31,Director,,0,0,0,,From this point on, the film was edited\Nto be increasingly implacable,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.44,1:50:34.53,Director,,0,0,0,,to instil a silence,\Neven in the dialogue.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.44,1:50:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll say goodbye here.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:39.36,1:50:41.99,Director,,0,0,0,,This is one of the rare moments\Nin the film
Dialogue: 0,1:50:42.12,1:50:46.62,Director,,0,0,0,,when the ends of the sequences\Nwere cut.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.75,1:50:48.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.67,1:50:55.05,Director,,0,0,0,,Some words spoken and filmed\Nwere removed.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:59.05,1:51:02.05,Director,,0,0,0,,This farewell sequence\Nwas particularly hard to shoot.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:02.18,1:51:06.10,Director,,0,0,0,,It just so happened that we'd drawn up\Na rather romantic schedule
Dialogue: 0,1:51:06.22,1:51:09.06,Director,,0,0,0,,so this was Adèle Haenel's last shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:09.19,1:51:16.78,Director,,0,0,0,,And the blood has completely drained\Nfrom Noémie Merlant's face.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:16.90,1:51:18.90,Director,,0,0,0,,She is as white as a sheet.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:20.20,1:51:21.74,Director,,0,0,0,,Because she's emotional.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:23.24,1:51:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have a safe journey.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:24.53,1:51:27.50,Director,,0,0,0,,The choreography was skilful\Nand complicated.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:29.46,1:51:30.71,Director,,0,0,0,,There's a tracking shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.75,1:51:33.38,Director,,0,0,0,,It stops and then starts again.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:34.25,1:51:37.38,Director,,0,0,0,,It was very hard to shoot because\Nwe were working with the real constraint
Dialogue: 0,1:51:37.51,1:51:39.47,Director,,0,0,0,,of the actresses having to part too.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:41.88,1:51:44.60,Director,,0,0,0,,The challenge with farewells\Nis getting the pace right.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.72,1:51:46.93,Director,,0,0,0,,The footsteps on the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:48.02,1:51:50.48,Director,,0,0,0,,The flight and the last image.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:50.60,1:51:52.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Turn around.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:52.90,1:51:54.02,Director,,0,0,0,,In the present.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.82,1:51:59.03,Director,,0,0,0,,We hear the sound effects\Nfrom the previous ghostly apparitions
Dialogue: 0,1:51:59.74,1:52:01.03,Director,,0,0,0,,made real.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:02.78,1:52:03.95,Director,,0,0,0,,And the door closing.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:11.58,1:52:13.04,Director,,0,0,0,,Back in the studio.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:14.25,1:52:18.46,Director,,0,0,0,,For the first\Nof the film's three endings.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:23.26,1:52:25.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've made me look so sad.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.10,1:52:31.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:32.64,1:52:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:40.82,1:52:43.99,Director,,0,0,0,,This landing strip\Nis actually a launching pad...
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.11,1:52:45.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I saw her again a first time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:47.41,1:52:48.83,Director,,0,0,0,,...for a first flashback.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.79,1:52:56.17,Director,,0,0,0,,There is lots of humour\Nin this scene full of extras,
Dialogue: 0,1:52:56.29,1:52:59.50,Director,,0,0,0,,shot in the studio,\Na reconstitution of the Paris salon.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:00.76,1:53:04.05,Director,,0,0,0,,With all these extras\Nit's like the film we could have made.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:06.47,1:53:12.52,Director,,0,0,0,,The painting behind Marianne\Nevokes the arch and the beach.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:12.64,1:53:15.02,Director,,0,0,0,,She herself is dressed\Nin the same colours as Orpheus
Dialogue: 0,1:53:15.10,1:53:18.52,Director,,0,0,0,,and Eurydice is wearing\Nthe white dress.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.65,1:53:20.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your father is in shape.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:20.40,1:53:23.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's my painting.\NI submitted it in his name.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:25.24,1:53:26.28,Director,,0,0,0,,A bit of mansplaining.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:26.41,1:53:29.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Usually, he's portrayed\Nbefore he turns
Dialogue: 0,1:53:29.41,1:53:31.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,or after, as Eurydice dies.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.41,1:53:35.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, they seem\Nto be saying goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:51.81,1:53:55.56,Director,,0,0,0,,I still wonder\Nwhether the audience really believes
Dialogue: 0,1:53:55.69,1:53:58.15,Director,,0,0,0,,we're about to see Héloïse,\Nbut I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.27,1:54:02.19,Director,,0,0,0,,I think they know it's a painting.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:07.99,1:54:10.37,Director,,0,0,0,,This is the last shot we filmed,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:10.49,1:54:12.99,Director,,0,0,0,,with Noémie looking at the painting.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:29.34,1:54:30.76,Director,,0,0,0,,The first blow to the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:33.06,1:54:34.18,Director,,0,0,0,,Page 28.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:34.97,1:54:37.81,Director,,0,0,0,,The language of the lovers\Nwhich is also the language of the film,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:37.94,1:54:41.15,Director,,0,0,0,,shared by the lovers in the film
Dialogue: 0,1:54:41.27,1:54:43.86,Director,,0,0,0,,and the audience in this sequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:43.98,1:54:45.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I saw her one last time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:45.82,1:54:46.94,Director,,0,0,0,,The reason we work.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:50.20,1:54:51.45,Director,,0,0,0,,This last scene...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:53.41,1:54:55.37,Director,,0,0,0,,...was the first one to be written.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.49,1:54:57.83,Director,,0,0,0,,It's the one I made the film for.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:02.13,1:55:03.71,Director,,0,0,0,,Theatre, indoors, night.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:04.63,1:55:07.80,Director,,0,0,0,,Marianne edges her way\Npast members of the audience
Dialogue: 0,1:55:08.84,1:55:11.05,Director,,0,0,0,,on a balcony\Nof an Italian-style theatre.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:15.26,1:55:18.73,Director,,0,0,0,,She sits down\Nand watches the room fill up
Dialogue: 0,1:55:19.77,1:55:22.52,Director,,0,0,0,,amidst the hubbub of voices,\Namplified by the acoustics
Dialogue: 0,1:55:22.65,1:55:24.19,Director,,0,0,0,,in the auditorium.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:35.95,1:55:39.71,Director,,0,0,0,,A familiar silhouette is making her way\Nalong the opposite balcony.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.00,1:55:45.63,Director,,0,0,0,,Her face is revealed\Nand Marianne is transfixed.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:49.17,1:55:50.26,Director,,0,0,0,,It's Héloïse.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:51.38,1:55:53.76,Director,,0,0,0,,She edges her way\Npast occupied and empty seats
Dialogue: 0,1:55:53.89,1:55:56.68,Director,,0,0,0,,until she reaches the end of the row,\Nlike the edge of a precipice.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:57.52,1:56:01.06,Director,,0,0,0,,She sits down.\NShe is right next to the stage.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:01.19,1:56:03.40,Director,,0,0,0,,She stares straight ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:03.52,1:56:06.07,Director,,0,0,0,,She doesn't look at the audience,\Nwhere the conversations fade,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:06.19,1:56:08.57,Director,,0,0,0,,one after the other,\Nas if by common consent.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:08.69,1:56:09.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She didn't see me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:09.99,1:56:11.53,Director,,0,0,0,,The theatre is gripped by a silence
Dialogue: 0,1:56:11.65,1:56:14.24,Director,,0,0,0,,just as violins strike up\Ntheir first thundery notes.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:18.83,1:56:21.12,Director,,0,0,0,,Like a held breath,\Npierced by a famous staccato.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:22.42,1:56:25.13,Director,,0,0,0,,The inaugural notes of the Presto\Nfrom Vivaldi's {\i0}"Summer".{\i1}
Dialogue: 0,1:56:27.21,1:56:30.88,Director,,0,0,0,,Héloïse looks troubled on hearing\Nthe opening bars of this longed-for piece.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:32.34,1:56:35.05,Director,,0,0,0,,We home in imperceptibly\Non her face
Dialogue: 0,1:56:35.18,1:56:37.51,Director,,0,0,0,,during the three minutes\Nthat the movement lasts.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:01.33,1:57:03.96,Director,,0,0,0,,Her face reflects\Nthe dramatic composition of the music
Dialogue: 0,1:57:04.08,1:57:05.50,Director,,0,0,0,,as she listens to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:06.33,1:57:08.79,Director,,0,0,0,,With its massive build-up of intensity,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:10.59,1:57:14.63,Director,,0,0,0,,it has everything:\NSurprise, exaltation,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:14.76,1:57:17.68,Director,,0,0,0,,a beating heart, expectation,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:17.80,1:57:21.10,Director,,0,0,0,,melancholy, concentration,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:21.22,1:57:23.35,Director,,0,0,0,,flushed cheeks,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:23.48,1:57:26.35,Director,,0,0,0,,memories, sadness,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:26.48,1:57:29.15,Director,,0,0,0,,and the breath deepening.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:41.66,1:57:43.54,Director,,0,0,0,,All the expressions of a woman
Dialogue: 0,1:57:43.66,1:57:47.29,Director,,0,0,0,,that we know well\Nand have enjoyed looking at,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:48.08,1:57:49.59,Director,,0,0,0,,that we have loved.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:50.84,1:57:54.80,Director,,0,0,0,,We also discover things\Nwe didn't know about her,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:54.88,1:57:58.22,Director,,0,0,0,,perhaps because they are new,\Nlike the lines in the corner of her eye,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:59.14,1:58:02.14,Director,,0,0,0,,perhaps also because\Nthey are things we haven't spotted
Dialogue: 0,1:58:02.26,1:58:04.27,Director,,0,0,0,,which remain to be understood.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:26.54,1:58:28.50,Director,,0,0,0,,When the piece reaches\Nits thrilling finale,
Dialogue: 0,1:58:30.88,1:58:35.17,Director,,0,0,0,,Héloïse reveals the last\Nand most alive of all her faces.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:46.85,1:58:50.48,Director,,0,0,0,,I gave Adèle just one direction:\NEnd with a gasp.
